98 void SourceCodeCache::Initialize(Isolate* isolate, bool create_heap_objects) {
99  cache_ = create_heap_objects ? ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array()
100  : Tagged<FixedArray>();
101 }
102 
103 void SourceCodeCache::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) {
104  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kExtensions, nullptr, FullObjectSlot(&cache_));
105 }
106 
107 bool SourceCodeCache::Lookup(Isolate* isolate, base::Vector<const char> name,
108  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>* handle) {
109  for (int i = 0; i < cache_->length(); i += 2) {
110  Tagged<SeqOneByteString> str = Cast<SeqOneByteString>(cache_->get(i));
111  if (str->IsOneByteEqualTo(name)) {
112  *handle =
113  direct_handle(Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(cache_->get(i + 1)), isolate);
114  return true;
115  }
116  }
117  return false;
118 }
119 
120 void SourceCodeCache::Add(Isolate* isolate, base::Vector<const char> name,
121  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
122  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
123  HandleScope scope(isolate);
124  int length = cache_->length();
125  DirectHandle<FixedArray> new_array =
126  factory->NewFixedArray(length + 2, AllocationType::kOld);
127  FixedArray::CopyElements(isolate, *new_array, 0, cache_, 0, cache_->length());
128  cache_ = *new_array;
129  DirectHandle<String> str =
130  factory
131  ->NewStringFromOneByte(base::Vector<const uint8_t>::cast(name),
132  AllocationType::kOld)
133  .ToHandleChecked();
134  DCHECK(!str.is_null());
135  cache_->set(length, *str);
136  cache_->set(length + 1, *shared);
137  Cast<Script>(shared->script())->set_type(type_);
138 }

140 Bootstrapper::Bootstrapper(Isolate* isolate)
141  : isolate_(isolate),
142  nesting_(0),
143  extensions_cache_(Script::Type::kExtension) {}

145 void Bootstrapper::Initialize(bool create_heap_objects) {
146  extensions_cache_.Initialize(isolate_, create_heap_objects);
147 }
148 
149 static const char* GCFunctionName() {
150  bool flag_given =
151  v8_flags.expose_gc_as != nullptr && strlen(v8_flags.expose_gc_as) != 0;
152  return flag_given ? v8_flags.expose_gc_as : "gc";
153 }
154 
155 static bool isValidCpuTraceMarkFunctionName() {
156  return v8_flags.expose_cputracemark_as != nullptr &&
157  strlen(v8_flags.expose_cputracemark_as) != 0;
158 }
159 
160 void Bootstrapper::InitializeOncePerProcess() {
161  v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<GCExtension>(GCFunctionName()));
162 #ifdef V8_FUZZILLI
163  v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<FuzzilliExtension>("fuzzilli"));
164 #endif
165  v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<ExternalizeStringExtension>());
166  v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<StatisticsExtension>());
167  v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<TriggerFailureExtension>());
168  v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<IgnitionStatisticsExtension>());
169  if (isValidCpuTraceMarkFunctionName()) {
170  v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<CpuTraceMarkExtension>(
171  v8_flags.expose_cputracemark_as));
172  }
173 #ifdef ENABLE_VTUNE_TRACEMARK
174  v8::RegisterExtension(
175  std::make_unique<VTuneDomainSupportExtension>("vtunedomainmark"));
176 #endif // ENABLE_VTUNE_TRACEMARK
177 }
178 
179 void Bootstrapper::TearDown() {
180  extensions_cache_.Initialize(isolate_, false); // Yes, symmetrical
181 }

183 class Genesis {

225  // Creates the global objects using the global proxy and the template passed
226  // in through the API. We call this regardless of whether we are building a
227  // context from scratch or using a deserialized one from the context snapshot
228  // but in the latter case we don't use the objects it produces directly, as
229  // we have to use the deserialized ones that are linked together with the
230  // rest of the context snapshot. At the end we link the global proxy and the
231  // context to each other.
232  DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> CreateNewGlobals(
233  v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
234  DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy);
235  // Similarly, we want to use the global that has been created by the templates
236  // passed through the API. The global from the snapshot is detached from the
237  // other objects in the snapshot.
238  void HookUpGlobalObject(DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object);
239  // Hooks the given global proxy into the context in the case we do not
240  // replace the global object from the deserialized native context.
241  void HookUpGlobalProxy(DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy);
242  // The native context has a ScriptContextTable that store declarative bindings
243  // made in script scopes. Add a "this" binding to that table pointing to the
244  // global proxy.
245  void InstallGlobalThisBinding();
246  // New context initialization. Used for creating a context from scratch.
247  void InitializeGlobal(DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object,
248  DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function);
249  void InitializeExperimentalGlobal();
250  void InitializeIteratorFunctions();
251  void InitializeCallSiteBuiltins();
252  void InitializeConsole(DirectHandle<JSObject> extras_binding);

345 void Bootstrapper::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) {
346  extensions_cache_.Iterate(v);
347  v->Synchronize(VisitorSynchronization::kExtensions);
348 }
349 
350 DirectHandle<NativeContext> Bootstrapper::CreateEnvironment(
351  MaybeDirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
352  v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
353  v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions, size_t context_snapshot_index,
354  DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
355  v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
356  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
357  DirectHandle<NativeContext> env;
358  {
359  Genesis genesis(isolate_, maybe_global_proxy, global_proxy_template,
360  context_snapshot_index, embedder_fields_deserializer,
361  microtask_queue);
362  env = genesis.result();
363  if (env.is_null() || !InstallExtensions(env, extensions)) {
364  return {};
365  }
366  }
367  LogAllMaps();
368  isolate_->heap()->NotifyBootstrapComplete();
369  return scope.CloseAndEscape(env);
370 }
371 
372 DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> Bootstrapper::NewRemoteContext(
373  MaybeDirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
374  v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template) {
375  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
376  DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy;
377  {
378  Genesis genesis(isolate_, maybe_global_proxy, global_proxy_template);
379  global_proxy = genesis.global_proxy();
380  if (global_proxy.is_null()) return {};
381  }
382  LogAllMaps();
383  return scope.CloseAndEscape(global_proxy);
384 }
385 
386 void Bootstrapper::LogAllMaps() {
387  if (!v8_flags.log_maps || isolate_->initialized_from_snapshot()) return;
388  // Log all created Map objects that are on the heap. For snapshots the Map
389  // logging happens during deserialization in order to avoid printing Maps
390  // multiple times during partial deserialization.
391  LOG(isolate_, LogAllMaps());
392 }

396 #ifdef DEBUG
397 bool IsFunctionMapOrSpecialBuiltin(DirectHandle<Map> map, Builtin builtin,
398  DirectHandle<Context> context) {
399  // During bootstrapping some of these maps could be not created yet.
400  return ((*map == context->GetNoCell(Context::STRICT_FUNCTION_MAP_INDEX)) ||
401  (*map == context->GetNoCell(
402  Context::STRICT_FUNCTION_WITHOUT_PROTOTYPE_MAP_INDEX)) ||
403  (*map ==
404  context->GetNoCell(
405  Context::STRICT_FUNCTION_WITH_READONLY_PROTOTYPE_MAP_INDEX)) ||
406  // Check if it's a creation of an empty or Proxy function during
407  // bootstrapping.
408  (builtin == Builtin::kEmptyFunction ||
409  builtin == Builtin::kProxyConstructor));
410 }
411 #endif // DEBUG
412 
413 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> CreateSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(
414  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, Builtin builtin, int len,
415  AdaptArguments adapt) {
416  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info =
417  isolate->factory()->NewSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(name, builtin, len,
418  adapt);
419  info->set_language_mode(LanguageMode::kStrict);
420 
421 #ifdef DEBUG
422  Tagged<Code> code = info->GetCode(isolate);
423  if (code->parameter_count() != kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel) {
424  DCHECK_EQ(info->internal_formal_parameter_count_with_receiver(),
425  code->parameter_count());
426  }
427 #endif
428 
429  return info;
430 }
431 
432 V8_NOINLINE DirectHandle<JSFunction> CreateFunctionForBuiltin(
433  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, DirectHandle<Map> map,
434  Builtin builtin, int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
435  DirectHandle<NativeContext> context(isolate->native_context());
436  DCHECK(IsFunctionMapOrSpecialBuiltin(map, builtin, context));
437 
438  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info =
439  CreateSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(isolate, name, builtin, len, adapt);
440 
441  return Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, info, context}
442  .set_map(map)
443  .Build();
444 }
445 
446 V8_NOINLINE DirectHandle<JSFunction> CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithPrototype(
447  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, Builtin builtin,
448  DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSPrototype, Hole>> prototype, InstanceType type,
449  int instance_size, int inobject_properties,
450  MutableMode prototype_mutability, int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
451  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
452  DirectHandle<NativeContext> context(isolate->native_context());
453  DirectHandle<Map> map =
454  prototype_mutability == MUTABLE
455  ? isolate->strict_function_map()
456  : isolate->strict_function_with_readonly_prototype_map();
457  DCHECK(IsFunctionMapOrSpecialBuiltin(map, builtin, context));
458 
459  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info =
460  CreateSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(isolate, name, builtin, len, adapt);
461  info->set_expected_nof_properties(inobject_properties);
462 
463  DirectHandle<JSFunction> result =
464  Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, info, context}.set_map(map).Build();
465 
466  ElementsKind elements_kind;
467  switch (type) {
468  case JS_ARRAY_TYPE:
469  elements_kind = PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS;
470  break;
471  case JS_ARGUMENTS_OBJECT_TYPE:
472  elements_kind = PACKED_ELEMENTS;
473  break;
474  default:
475  elements_kind = TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND;
476  break;
477  }
478  DirectHandle<Map> initial_map = factory->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
479  type, instance_size, elements_kind, inobject_properties);
480  initial_map->SetConstructor(*result);
481  if (type == JS_FUNCTION_TYPE) {
482  DCHECK_EQ(instance_size, JSFunction::kSizeWithPrototype);
483  // Since we are creating an initial map for JSFunction objects with
484  // prototype slot, set the respective bit.
485  initial_map->set_has_prototype_slot(true);
486  }
487  // TODO(littledan): Why do we have this is_generator test when
488  // NewFunctionPrototype already handles finding an appropriately
489  // shared prototype?
490  if (!IsResumableFunction(info->kind()) && IsTheHole(*prototype, isolate)) {
491  prototype = factory->NewFunctionPrototype(result);
492  }
493  JSFunction::SetInitialMap(isolate, result, initial_map,
494  Cast<JSPrototype>(prototype));
495 
496  return result;
497 }
498 
499 V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithoutPrototype(
500  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, Builtin builtin, int len,
501  AdaptArguments adapt) {
502  DirectHandle<NativeContext> context(isolate->native_context());
503  DirectHandle<Map> map = isolate->strict_function_without_prototype_map();
504  DCHECK(IsFunctionMapOrSpecialBuiltin(map, builtin, context));
505 
506  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info =
507  CreateSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(isolate, name, builtin, len, adapt);
508 
509  return Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, info, context}
510  .set_map(map)
511  .Build();
512 }
513 
514 V8_NOINLINE DirectHandle<JSFunction> CreateFunction(
515  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, InstanceType type,
516  int instance_size, int inobject_properties,
517  DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSPrototype, Hole>> prototype, Builtin builtin,
518  int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
519  DCHECK(Builtins::HasJSLinkage(builtin));
520 
521  DirectHandle<JSFunction> result = CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithPrototype(
522  isolate, name, builtin, prototype, type, instance_size,
523  inobject_properties, IMMUTABLE, len, adapt);
524 
525  // Make the JSFunction's prototype object fast.
526  JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(direct_handle(result->prototype(), isolate),
527  kStartAtReceiver, isolate);
528 
529  // Make the resulting JSFunction object fast.
530  JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(result, kStartAtReceiver, isolate);
531  result->shared()->set_native(true);
532  return result;
533 }
534 
535 V8_NOINLINE DirectHandle<JSFunction> CreateFunction(
536  Isolate* isolate, const char* name, InstanceType type, int instance_size,
537  int inobject_properties, DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSPrototype, Hole>> prototype,
538  Builtin builtin, int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
539  return CreateFunction(
540  isolate, isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name), type,
541  instance_size, inobject_properties, prototype, builtin, len, adapt);
542 }
543 
544 V8_NOINLINE DirectHandle<JSFunction> InstallFunction(
545  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> target, DirectHandle<String> name,
546  InstanceType type, int instance_size, int inobject_properties,
547  DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSPrototype, Hole>> prototype, Builtin call, int len,
548  AdaptArguments adapt) {
549  DCHECK(Builtins::HasJSLinkage(call));
550  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function =
551  CreateFunction(isolate, name, type, instance_size, inobject_properties,
552  prototype, call, len, adapt);
553  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, target, name, function, DONT_ENUM);
554  return function;
555 }
556 
557 V8_NOINLINE DirectHandle<JSFunction> InstallFunction(
558  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> target, const char* name,
559  InstanceType type, int instance_size, int inobject_properties,
560  DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSPrototype, Hole>> prototype, Builtin call, int len,
561  AdaptArguments adapt) {
562  return InstallFunction(
563  isolate, target, isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name), type,
564  instance_size, inobject_properties, prototype, call, len, adapt);
565 }
566 
567 // This sets a constructor instance type on the constructor map which will be
568 // used in IsXxxConstructor() predicates. Having such predicates helps figuring
569 // out if a protector cell should be invalidated. If there are no protector
570 // cell checks required for constructor, this function must not be used.
571 // Note, this function doesn't create a copy of the constructor's map. So it's
572 // better to set constructor instance type after all the properties are added
573 // to the constructor and thus the map is already guaranteed to be unique.
574 V8_NOINLINE void SetConstructorInstanceType(
575  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor,
576  InstanceType constructor_type) {
577  DCHECK(InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(constructor_type));
578  DCHECK_NE(constructor_type, JS_FUNCTION_TYPE);
579 
580  Tagged<Map> map = constructor->map();
581 
582  // Check we don't accidentally change one of the existing maps.
583  DCHECK_NE(map, *isolate->strict_function_map());
584  DCHECK_NE(map, *isolate->strict_function_with_readonly_prototype_map());
585  // Constructor function map is always a root map, and thus we don't have to
586  // deal with updating the whole transition tree.
587  DCHECK(IsUndefined(map->GetBackPointer(), isolate));
588  DCHECK_EQ(JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, map->instance_type());
589 
590  map->set_instance_type(constructor_type);
591 }
592 
593 V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> SimpleCreateFunction(Isolate* isolate,
594  DirectHandle<String> name,
595  Builtin call, int len,
596  AdaptArguments adapt) {
597  DCHECK(Builtins::HasJSLinkage(call));
598  name = String::Flatten(isolate, name, AllocationType::kOld);
599  Handle<JSFunction> fun =
600  CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithoutPrototype(isolate, name, call, len, adapt);
601  // Make the resulting JSFunction object fast.
602  JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(fun, kStartAtReceiver, isolate);
603  fun->shared()->set_native(true);
604  return fun;
605 }
606 
607 V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(
608  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> base, const char* name,
609  Builtin call, int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
610  DirectHandle<String> internalized_name =
611  isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name);
612  Handle<JSFunction> fun =
613  SimpleCreateFunction(isolate, internalized_name, call, len, adapt);
614  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, base, internalized_name, fun, DONT_ENUM);
615  return fun;
616 }

618 V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> InstallFunctionAtSymbol(
619  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> base, DirectHandle<Symbol> symbol,
620  const char* symbol_string, Builtin call, int len, AdaptArguments adapt,
621  PropertyAttributes attrs = DONT_ENUM) {
622  DirectHandle<String> internalized_symbol =
623  isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(symbol_string);
624  Handle<JSFunction> fun =
625  SimpleCreateFunction(isolate, internalized_symbol, call, len, adapt);
626  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, base, symbol, fun, attrs);

630 V8_NOINLINE DirectHandle<JSFunction> CreateSharedObjectConstructor(
631  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, DirectHandle<Map> instance_map,
632  Builtin builtin, int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
633  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
634  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info =
635  factory->NewSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(name, builtin, len, adapt);
636  info->set_language_mode(LanguageMode::kStrict);
637  DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor =
638  Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, info, isolate->native_context()}
639  .set_map(isolate->strict_function_with_readonly_prototype_map())
640  .Build();
641  constructor->set_prototype_or_initial_map(*instance_map, kReleaseStore);
642 
643  JSObject::AddProperty(
644  isolate, constructor, factory->has_instance_symbol(),
645  direct_handle(
646  isolate->native_context()->shared_space_js_object_has_instance(),
647  isolate),
648  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY));
649  return constructor;
650 }

652 V8_NOINLINE void SimpleInstallGetterSetter(Isolate* isolate,
653  DirectHandle<JSObject> base,
654  DirectHandle<Name> name,
655  Builtin call_getter,
656  Builtin call_setter) {
657  DirectHandle<String> getter_name =
658  Name::ToFunctionName(isolate, name, isolate->factory()->get_string())
659  .ToHandleChecked();
660  DirectHandle<JSFunction> getter =
661  SimpleCreateFunction(isolate, getter_name, call_getter, 0, kAdapt);
662 
663  DirectHandle<String> setter_name =
664  Name::ToFunctionName(isolate, name, isolate->factory()->set_string())
665  .ToHandleChecked();
666  DirectHandle<JSFunction> setter =
667  SimpleCreateFunction(isolate, setter_name, call_setter, 1, kAdapt);
668 
669  JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(base, name, getter, setter,
670  DONT_ENUM)
671  .Check();
672 }

674 void SimpleInstallGetterSetter(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> base,
675  const char* name, Builtin call_getter,
676  Builtin call_setter) {
677  SimpleInstallGetterSetter(isolate, base,
678  isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name),
679  call_getter, call_setter);
680 }

682 V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> SimpleInstallGetter(
683  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> base, DirectHandle<Name> name,
684  DirectHandle<Name> property_name, Builtin call, AdaptArguments adapt) {
685  DirectHandle<String> getter_name =
686  Name::ToFunctionName(isolate, name, isolate->factory()->get_string())
687  .ToHandleChecked();
688  Handle<JSFunction> getter =
689  SimpleCreateFunction(isolate, getter_name, call, 0, adapt);
690 
691  DirectHandle<Object> setter = isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
692 
693  JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(base, property_name, getter,
694  setter, DONT_ENUM)
695  .Check();
696 
697  return getter;
698 }

748 // Create a map for result objects returned from builtins in such a way that
749 // it's exactly the same map as the one produced by object literals. E.g.,
750 // iterator result objects have the same map as literals in the form `{value,
751 // done}`.
752 //
753 // This way we have better sharing of maps (i.e. less polymorphism) and also
754 // make it possible to hit the fast-paths in various builtins (i.e. promises and
755 // collections) with user defined iterators.
756 template <size_t N>
757 DirectHandle<Map> CreateLiteralObjectMapFromCache(
758  Isolate* isolate, const std::array<DirectHandle<Name>, N>& properties) {
759  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
760  DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context = isolate->native_context();
761  DirectHandle<Map> map = factory->ObjectLiteralMapFromCache(native_context, N);
762  for (DirectHandle<Name> name : properties) {
763  map = Map::CopyWithField(isolate, map, name, FieldType::Any(isolate), NONE,
764  PropertyConstness::kConst,
765  Representation::Tagged(), INSERT_TRANSITION)
766  .ToHandleChecked();
767  }
768  return map;
769 }
770 
771 } // namespace
772 
773 DirectHandle<JSFunction> Genesis::CreateEmptyFunction() {
774  // Allocate the function map first and then patch the prototype later.
775  DirectHandle<Map> empty_function_map =
776  factory()->CreateSloppyFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITHOUT_PROTOTYPE, {});
777  empty_function_map->set_is_prototype_map(true);
778  DCHECK(!empty_function_map->is_dictionary_map());
779 
780  // Allocate the empty function as the prototype for function according to
781  // ES#sec-properties-of-the-function-prototype-object
782  DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function = CreateFunctionForBuiltin(
783  isolate(), factory()->empty_string(), empty_function_map,
784  Builtin::kEmptyFunction, 0, kDontAdapt);
785  empty_function_map->SetConstructor(*empty_function);
786  native_context()->set_empty_function(*empty_function);
787 
788  // --- E m p t y ---
789  DirectHandle<String> source = factory()->InternalizeString("() {}");
790  DirectHandle<Script> script = factory()->NewScript(source);
791  script->set_type(Script::Type::kNative);
792  DirectHandle<WeakFixedArray> infos = factory()->NewWeakFixedArray(2);
793  script->set_infos(*infos);
794  ReadOnlyRoots roots{isolate()};
795  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = empty_function->shared();
796  sfi->set_raw_scope_info(roots.empty_function_scope_info());
797  sfi->SetScript(isolate(), roots, *script, 1);
798  sfi->UpdateFunctionMapIndex();
799 
800  return empty_function;
801 }
802 
803 void Genesis::CreateSloppyModeFunctionMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
804  Factory* factory = isolate_->factory();
805  DirectHandle<Map> map;
806 
807  //
808  // Allocate maps for sloppy functions without prototype.
809  //
810  map = factory->CreateSloppyFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITHOUT_PROTOTYPE, empty);
811  native_context()->set_sloppy_function_without_prototype_map(*map);
812 
813  //
814  // Allocate maps for sloppy functions with readonly prototype.
815  //
816  map =
817  factory->CreateSloppyFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITH_READONLY_PROTOTYPE, empty);
818  native_context()->set_sloppy_function_with_readonly_prototype_map(*map);
819 
820  //
821  // Allocate maps for sloppy functions with writable prototype.
822  //
823  map = factory->CreateSloppyFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITH_WRITEABLE_PROTOTYPE,
824  empty);
825  native_context()->set_sloppy_function_map(*map);
826 
827  map = factory->CreateSloppyFunctionMap(
828  FUNCTION_WITH_NAME_AND_WRITEABLE_PROTOTYPE, empty);
829  native_context()->set_sloppy_function_with_name_map(*map);
830 }
831 
832 DirectHandle<JSFunction> Genesis::GetThrowTypeErrorIntrinsic() {
833  if (!restricted_properties_thrower_.is_null()) {
834  return restricted_properties_thrower_;
835  }
836  DirectHandle<String> name = factory()->empty_string();
837  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithoutPrototype(
838  isolate(), name, Builtin::kStrictPoisonPillThrower, 0, kAdapt);
839 
840  // %ThrowTypeError% must have a name property with an empty string value. Per
841  // spec, ThrowTypeError's name is non-configurable, unlike ordinary functions'
842  // name property. To redefine it to be non-configurable, use
843  // SetOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes.
844  JSObject::SetOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
845  function, factory()->name_string(), factory()->empty_string(),
846  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY))
847  .Assert();
848 
849  // length needs to be non configurable.
850  DirectHandle<Object> value(Smi::FromInt(function->length()), isolate());
851  JSObject::SetOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
852  function, factory()->length_string(), value,
853  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY))
854  .Assert();
855 
856  if (JSObject::PreventExtensions(isolate_, function, kThrowOnError)
857  .IsNothing()) {
858  DCHECK(false);
859  }
860 
861  JSObject::MigrateSlowToFast(function, 0, "Bootstrapping");
862 
863  restricted_properties_thrower_ = function;
864  return function;
865 }
866 
867 void Genesis::CreateStrictModeFunctionMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
868  Factory* factory = isolate_->factory();
869  DirectHandle<Map> map;
870 
871  //
872  // Allocate maps for strict functions without prototype.
873  //
874  map = factory->CreateStrictFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITHOUT_PROTOTYPE, empty);
875  native_context()->set_strict_function_without_prototype_map(*map);
876 
877  map = factory->CreateStrictFunctionMap(METHOD_WITH_NAME, empty);
878  native_context()->set_method_with_name_map(*map);
879 
880  //
881  // Allocate maps for strict functions with writable prototype.
882  //
883  map = factory->CreateStrictFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITH_WRITEABLE_PROTOTYPE,
884  empty);
885  native_context()->set_strict_function_map(*map);
886 
887  map = factory->CreateStrictFunctionMap(
888  FUNCTION_WITH_NAME_AND_WRITEABLE_PROTOTYPE, empty);
889  native_context()->set_strict_function_with_name_map(*map);
890 
891  //
892  // Allocate maps for strict functions with readonly prototype.
893  //
894  map =
895  factory->CreateStrictFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITH_READONLY_PROTOTYPE, empty);
896  native_context()->set_strict_function_with_readonly_prototype_map(*map);
897 
898  //
899  // Allocate map for class functions.
900  //
901  map = factory->CreateClassFunctionMap(empty);
902  native_context()->set_class_function_map(*map);
903 
904 #ifdef V8_FUNCTION_ARGUMENTS_CALLER_ARE_OWN_PROPS
905  // Now that the strict mode function map is available, set up the
906  // restricted "arguments" and "caller" getters.
907  AddRestrictedFunctionProperties(empty);
908 #endif // V8_FUNCTION_ARGUMENTS_CALLER_ARE_OWN_PROPS
909 }
910 
911 void Genesis::CreateObjectFunction(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function) {
912  Factory* factory = isolate_->factory();
913 
914  // --- O b j e c t ---
915  int inobject_properties = JSObject::kInitialGlobalObjectUnusedPropertiesCount;
916  int instance_size = JSObject::kHeaderSize + kTaggedSize * inobject_properties;
917 
918  DirectHandle<JSFunction> object_fun =
919  CreateFunction(isolate_, factory->Object_string(), JS_OBJECT_TYPE,
920  instance_size, inobject_properties, factory->null_value(),
921  Builtin::kObjectConstructor, 1, kDontAdapt);
922  native_context()->set_object_function(*object_fun);
923 
924  {
925  // Finish setting up Object function's initial map.
926  Tagged<Map> initial_map = object_fun->initial_map();
927  initial_map->set_elements_kind(HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
928  }
929 
930  // Allocate a new prototype for the object function.
931  DirectHandle<JSObject> object_function_prototype =
932  factory->NewFunctionPrototype(object_fun);
933 
934  {
935  DirectHandle<Map> map = Map::Copy(
936  isolate(), direct_handle(object_function_prototype->map(), isolate()),
937  "EmptyObjectPrototype");
938  map->set_is_prototype_map(true);
939  // Ban re-setting Object.prototype.__proto__ to prevent Proxy security bug
940  map->set_is_immutable_proto(true);
941  object_function_prototype->set_map(isolate(), *map);
942  }
943 
944  // Complete setting up empty function.
945  {
946  DirectHandle<Map> empty_function_map(empty_function->map(), isolate_);
947  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), empty_function_map, object_function_prototype);
948  }
949 
950  native_context()->set_initial_object_prototype(*object_function_prototype);
951  JSFunction::SetPrototype(isolate_, object_fun, object_function_prototype);
952  object_function_prototype->map()->set_instance_type(JS_OBJECT_PROTOTYPE_TYPE);
953  {
954  // Set up slow map for Object.create(null) instances without in-object
955  // properties.
956  DirectHandle<Map> map(object_fun->initial_map(), isolate_);
957  map = Map::CopyInitialMapNormalized(isolate(), map);
958  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, factory->null_value());
959  native_context()->set_slow_object_with_null_prototype_map(*map);
960 
961  // Set up slow map for literals with too many properties.
962  map = Map::Copy(isolate(), map, "slow_object_with_object_prototype_map");
963  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, object_function_prototype);
964  native_context()->set_slow_object_with_object_prototype_map(*map);
965  }
966 }
967 
968 namespace {
969 
970 DirectHandle<Map> CreateNonConstructorMap(Isolate* isolate,
971  DirectHandle<Map> source_map,
972  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype,
973  const char* reason) {
974  DirectHandle<Map> map = Map::Copy(isolate, source_map, reason);
975  // Ensure the resulting map has prototype slot (it is necessary for storing
976  // initial map even when the prototype property is not required).
977  if (!map->has_prototype_slot()) {
978  // Re-set the unused property fields after changing the instance size.
979  int unused_property_fields = map->UnusedPropertyFields();
980  map->set_instance_size(map->instance_size() + kTaggedSize);
981  // The prototype slot shifts the in-object properties area by one slot.
982  map->SetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords(
983  map->GetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords() + 1);
984  map->set_has_prototype_slot(true);
985  map->SetInObjectUnusedPropertyFields(unused_property_fields);
986  }
987  map->set_is_constructor(false);
988  Map::SetPrototype(isolate, map, prototype);
989  return map;
990 }
991 
992 } // namespace
993 
994 Handle<JSFunction> SimpleInstallFunction(Isolate* isolate,
995  DirectHandle<JSObject> base,
996  const char* name, Builtin call,
997  int len, AdaptArguments adapt,
998  PropertyAttributes attrs) {
999  // Although function name does not have to be internalized the property name
1000  // will be internalized during property addition anyway, so do it here now.
1001  DirectHandle<String> internalized_name =
1002  isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name);
1003  Handle<JSFunction> fun =
1004  SimpleCreateFunction(isolate, internalized_name, call, len, adapt);
1005  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, base, internalized_name, fun, attrs);
1006  return fun;
1007 }

1009 void Genesis::CreateIteratorMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
1010  // Create iterator-related meta-objects.
1011  DirectHandle<JSObject> iterator_prototype = factory()->NewJSObject(
1012  isolate()->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1013 
1014  InstallFunctionAtSymbol(isolate(), iterator_prototype,
1015  factory()->iterator_symbol(), "[Symbol.iterator]",
1016  Builtin::kReturnReceiver, 0, kAdapt);
1017  native_context()->set_initial_iterator_prototype(*iterator_prototype);
1018  CHECK_NE(iterator_prototype->map().ptr(),
1019  isolate_->initial_object_prototype()->map().ptr());
1020  iterator_prototype->map()->set_instance_type(JS_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE);
1021 
1022  DirectHandle<JSObject> generator_object_prototype = factory()->NewJSObject(
1023  isolate()->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1024  native_context()->set_initial_generator_prototype(
1025  *generator_object_prototype);
1026  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), generator_object_prototype,
1027  iterator_prototype);
1028  DirectHandle<JSObject> generator_function_prototype = factory()->NewJSObject(
1029  isolate()->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1030  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), generator_function_prototype, empty);
1031 
1032  InstallToStringTag(isolate(), generator_function_prototype,
1033  "GeneratorFunction");
1034  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), generator_function_prototype,
1035  factory()->prototype_string(),
1036  generator_object_prototype,
1037  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY));
1038 
1039  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), generator_object_prototype,
1040  factory()->constructor_string(),
1041  generator_function_prototype,
1042  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY));
1043  InstallToStringTag(isolate(), generator_object_prototype, "Generator");
1044  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), generator_object_prototype, "next",
1045  Builtin::kGeneratorPrototypeNext, 1, kDontAdapt);
1046  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), generator_object_prototype, "return",
1047  Builtin::kGeneratorPrototypeReturn, 1, kDontAdapt);
1048  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), generator_object_prototype, "throw",
1049  Builtin::kGeneratorPrototypeThrow, 1, kDontAdapt);
1050 
1051  // Internal version of generator_prototype_next, flagged as non-native such
1052  // that it doesn't show up in Error traces.
1053  DirectHandle<JSFunction> generator_next_internal =
1054  SimpleCreateFunction(isolate(), factory()->next_string(),
1055  Builtin::kGeneratorPrototypeNext, 1, kDontAdapt);
1056  generator_next_internal->shared()->set_native(false);
1057  native_context()->set_generator_next_internal(*generator_next_internal);
1058 
1059  // Internal version of async module functions, flagged as non-native such
1060  // that they don't show up in Error traces.
1061  {
1062  DirectHandle<JSFunction> async_module_evaluate_internal =
1063  SimpleCreateFunction(isolate(), factory()->next_string(),
1064  Builtin::kAsyncModuleEvaluate, 1, kDontAdapt);
1065  async_module_evaluate_internal->shared()->set_native(false);
1066  native_context()->set_async_module_evaluate_internal(
1067  *async_module_evaluate_internal);
1068  }
1069 
1070  // Create maps for generator functions and their prototypes. Store those
1071  // maps in the native context. The "prototype" property descriptor is
1072  // writable, non-enumerable, and non-configurable (as per ES6 draft
1073  // 04-14-15, section 25.2.4.3).
1074  // Generator functions do not have "caller" or "arguments" accessors.
1075  DirectHandle<Map> map;
1076  map = CreateNonConstructorMap(isolate(), isolate()->strict_function_map(),
1077  generator_function_prototype,
1078  "GeneratorFunction");
1079  native_context()->set_generator_function_map(*map);
1080 
1081  map = CreateNonConstructorMap(
1082  isolate(), isolate()->strict_function_with_name_map(),
1083  generator_function_prototype, "GeneratorFunction with name");
1084  native_context()->set_generator_function_with_name_map(*map);
1085 
1086  DirectHandle<JSFunction> object_function(native_context()->object_function(),
1087  isolate());
1088  DirectHandle<Map> generator_object_prototype_map = Map::Create(isolate(), 0);
1089  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), generator_object_prototype_map,
1090  generator_object_prototype);
1091  native_context()->set_generator_object_prototype_map(
1092  *generator_object_prototype_map);
1093 }
1094 
1095 void Genesis::CreateAsyncIteratorMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
1096  // %AsyncIteratorPrototype%
1097  // proposal-async-iteration/#sec-asynciteratorprototype
1098  DirectHandle<JSObject> async_iterator_prototype = factory()->NewJSObject(
1099  isolate()->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1100 
1101  InstallFunctionAtSymbol(
1102  isolate(), async_iterator_prototype, factory()->async_iterator_symbol(),
1103  "[Symbol.asyncIterator]", Builtin::kReturnReceiver, 0, kAdapt);
1104  native_context()->set_initial_async_iterator_prototype(
1105  *async_iterator_prototype);
1106 
1107  // %AsyncFromSyncIteratorPrototype%
1108  // proposal-async-iteration/#sec-%asyncfromsynciteratorprototype%-object
1109  DirectHandle<JSObject> async_from_sync_iterator_prototype =
1110  factory()->NewJSObject(isolate()->object_function(),
1111  AllocationType::kOld);
1112  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_prototype, "next",
1113  Builtin::kAsyncFromSyncIteratorPrototypeNext, 1,
1114  kDontAdapt);
1115  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_prototype, "return",
1116  Builtin::kAsyncFromSyncIteratorPrototypeReturn, 1,
1117  kDontAdapt);
1118  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_prototype, "throw",
1119  Builtin::kAsyncFromSyncIteratorPrototypeThrow, 1,
1120  kDontAdapt);
1121 
1122  InstallToStringTag(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_prototype,
1123  "Async-from-Sync Iterator");
1124 
1125  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_prototype,
1126  async_iterator_prototype);
1127 
1128  DirectHandle<Map> async_from_sync_iterator_map =
1129  factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
1130  JS_ASYNC_FROM_SYNC_ITERATOR_TYPE,
1131  JSAsyncFromSyncIterator::kHeaderSize);
1132  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_map,
1133  async_from_sync_iterator_prototype);
1134  native_context()->set_async_from_sync_iterator_map(
1135  *async_from_sync_iterator_map);
1136 
1137  // Async Generators
1138  DirectHandle<JSObject> async_generator_object_prototype =
1139  factory()->NewJSObject(isolate()->object_function(),
1140  AllocationType::kOld);
1141  DirectHandle<JSObject> async_generator_function_prototype =
1142  factory()->NewJSObject(isolate()->object_function(),
1143  AllocationType::kOld);
1144 
1145  // %AsyncGenerator% / %AsyncGeneratorFunction%.prototype
1146  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), async_generator_function_prototype,
1147  empty);
1148 
1149  // The value of AsyncGeneratorFunction.prototype.prototype is the
1150  // %AsyncGeneratorPrototype% intrinsic object.
1151  // This property has the attributes
1152  // { [[Writable]]: false, [[Enumerable]]: false, [[Configurable]]: true }.
1153  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), async_generator_function_prototype,
1154  factory()->prototype_string(),
1155  async_generator_object_prototype,
1156  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY));
1157  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype,
1158  factory()->constructor_string(),
1159  async_generator_function_prototype,
1160  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY));
1161  InstallToStringTag(isolate(), async_generator_function_prototype,
1162  "AsyncGeneratorFunction");
1163 
1164  // %AsyncGeneratorPrototype%
1165  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype,
1166  async_iterator_prototype);
1167  native_context()->set_initial_async_generator_prototype(
1168  *async_generator_object_prototype);
1169 
1170  InstallToStringTag(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype,
1171  "AsyncGenerator");
1172  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype, "next",
1173  Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorPrototypeNext, 1, kDontAdapt);
1174  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype, "return",
1175  Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorPrototypeReturn, 1, kDontAdapt);
1176  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype, "throw",
1177  Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorPrototypeThrow, 1, kDontAdapt);
1178 
1179  // Create maps for generator functions and their prototypes. Store those
1180  // maps in the native context. The "prototype" property descriptor is
1181  // writable, non-enumerable, and non-configurable (as per ES6 draft
1182  // 04-14-15, section 25.2.4.3).
1183  // Async Generator functions do not have "caller" or "arguments" accessors.
1184  DirectHandle<Map> map;
1185  map = CreateNonConstructorMap(isolate(), isolate()->strict_function_map(),
1186  async_generator_function_prototype,
1187  "AsyncGeneratorFunction");
1188  native_context()->set_async_generator_function_map(*map);
1189 
1190  map = CreateNonConstructorMap(
1191  isolate(), isolate()->strict_function_with_name_map(),
1192  async_generator_function_prototype, "AsyncGeneratorFunction with name");
1193  native_context()->set_async_generator_function_with_name_map(*map);
1194 
1195  DirectHandle<JSFunction> object_function(native_context()->object_function(),
1196  isolate());
1197  DirectHandle<Map> async_generator_object_prototype_map =
1198  Map::Create(isolate(), 0);
1199  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype_map,
1200  async_generator_object_prototype);
1201  native_context()->set_async_generator_object_prototype_map(
1202  *async_generator_object_prototype_map);
1203 }
1204 
1205 void Genesis::CreateAsyncFunctionMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
1206  // %AsyncFunctionPrototype% intrinsic
1207  DirectHandle<JSObject> async_function_prototype = factory()->NewJSObject(
1208  isolate()->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1209  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), async_function_prototype, empty);
1210 
1211  InstallToStringTag(isolate(), async_function_prototype, "AsyncFunction");
1212 
1213  DirectHandle<Map> map =
1214  Map::Copy(isolate(), isolate()->strict_function_without_prototype_map(),
1215  "AsyncFunction");
1216  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, async_function_prototype);
1217  native_context()->set_async_function_map(*map);
1218 
1219  map = Map::Copy(isolate(), isolate()->method_with_name_map(),
1220  "AsyncFunction with name");
1221  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, async_function_prototype);
1222  native_context()->set_async_function_with_name_map(*map);
1223 }

1225 void Genesis::CreateJSProxyMaps() {
1226  // Allocate maps for all Proxy types.
1227  // Next to the default proxy, we need maps indicating callable and
1228  // constructable proxies.
1229  DirectHandle<Map> proxy_map = factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
1230  JS_PROXY_TYPE, JSProxy::kSize, TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND);
1231  proxy_map->set_is_dictionary_map(true);
1232  proxy_map->set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
1233  native_context()->set_proxy_map(*proxy_map);
1234  proxy_map->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
1235 
1236  DirectHandle<Map> proxy_callable_map =
1237  Map::Copy(isolate_, proxy_map, "callable Proxy");
1238  proxy_callable_map->set_is_callable(true);
1239  native_context()->set_proxy_callable_map(*proxy_callable_map);
1240  proxy_callable_map->SetConstructor(native_context()->function_function());
1241 
1242  DirectHandle<Map> proxy_constructor_map =
1243  Map::Copy(isolate_, proxy_callable_map, "constructor Proxy");
1244  proxy_constructor_map->set_is_constructor(true);
1245  native_context()->set_proxy_constructor_map(*proxy_constructor_map);
1246 
1247  {
1248  DirectHandle<Map> map = factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
1249  JS_OBJECT_TYPE, JSProxyRevocableResult::kSize,
1250  TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, 2);
1251  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate_, map, 2);
1252 
1253  { // proxy
1254  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->proxy_string(),
1255  JSProxyRevocableResult::kProxyIndex,
1256  NONE, Representation::Tagged());
1257  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
1258  }
1259  { // revoke
1260  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
1261  isolate(), factory()->revoke_string(),
1262  JSProxyRevocableResult::kRevokeIndex, NONE, Representation::Tagged());
1263  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
1264  }
1265 
1266  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, isolate()->initial_object_prototype());
1267  map->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
1268 
1269  native_context()->set_proxy_revocable_result_map(*map);
1270  }
1271 }

1273 namespace {
1274 void ReplaceAccessors(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Map> map,
1275  DirectHandle<String> name, PropertyAttributes attributes,
1276  DirectHandle<AccessorPair> accessor_pair) {
1277  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = map->instance_descriptors(isolate);
1278  InternalIndex entry = descriptors->SearchWithCache(isolate, *name, *map);
1279  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(name, accessor_pair, attributes);
1280  descriptors->Replace(entry, &d);
1281 }
1282 
1283 void InitializeJSArrayMaps(Isolate* isolate,
1284  DirectHandle<Context> native_context,
1285  DirectHandle<Map> initial_map) {
1286  // Replace all of the cached initial array maps in the native context with
1287  // the appropriate transitioned elements kind maps.
1288  DirectHandle<Map> current_map = initial_map;
1289  ElementsKind kind = current_map->elements_kind();
1290  DCHECK_EQ(GetInitialFastElementsKind(), kind);
1291  DCHECK_EQ(PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS, kind);
1292  DCHECK_EQ(Context::ArrayMapIndex(kind),
1293  Context::JS_ARRAY_PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS_MAP_INDEX);
1294  native_context->SetNoCell(Context::ArrayMapIndex(kind), *current_map,
1295  kReleaseStore);
1296  for (int i = GetSequenceIndexFromFastElementsKind(kind) + 1;
1297  i < kFastElementsKindCount; ++i) {
1298  DirectHandle<Map> new_map;
1299  ElementsKind next_kind = GetFastElementsKindFromSequenceIndex(i);
1300  Tagged<Map> maybe_elements_transition = current_map->ElementsTransitionMap(
1301  isolate, ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
1302  if (!maybe_elements_transition.is_null()) {
1303  new_map = direct_handle(maybe_elements_transition, isolate);
1304  } else {
1305  new_map = Map::CopyAsElementsKind(isolate, current_map, next_kind,
1306  INSERT_TRANSITION);
1307  }
1308  DCHECK_EQ(next_kind, new_map->elements_kind());
1309  native_context->SetNoCell(Context::ArrayMapIndex(next_kind), *new_map,
1310  kReleaseStore);
1311  current_map = new_map;
1312  }
1313 }
1314 } // namespace

1316 void Genesis::AddRestrictedFunctionProperties(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
1317  PropertyAttributes rw_attribs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM);
1318  DirectHandle<JSFunction> thrower = GetThrowTypeErrorIntrinsic();
1319  DirectHandle<AccessorPair> accessors = factory()->NewAccessorPair();
1320  accessors->set_getter(*thrower);
1321  accessors->set_setter(*thrower);
1322 
1323  DirectHandle<Map> map(empty->map(), isolate());
1324  ReplaceAccessors(isolate(), map, factory()->arguments_string(), rw_attribs,
1325  accessors);
1326  ReplaceAccessors(isolate(), map, factory()->caller_string(), rw_attribs,
1327  accessors);
1328 }

1330 static void AddToWeakNativeContextList(Isolate* isolate,
1331  Tagged<Context> context) {
1332  DCHECK(IsNativeContext(context));
1333  Heap* heap = isolate->heap();
1334 #ifdef DEBUG
1335  {
1336  DCHECK(IsUndefined(context->next_context_link(), isolate));
1337  // Check that context is not in the list yet.
1338  for (Tagged<Object> current = heap->native_contexts_list();
1339  !IsUndefined(current, isolate);
1340  current = Cast<Context>(current)->next_context_link()) {
1341  DCHECK(current != context);
1342  }
1343  }
1344 #endif
1345  context->SetNoCell(Context::NEXT_CONTEXT_LINK, heap->native_contexts_list(),
1346  UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
1347  heap->set_native_contexts_list(context);
1348 }

1350 void Genesis::CreateRoots() {
1351  // Allocate the native context FixedArray first and then patch the
1352  // closure and extension object later (we need the empty function
1353  // and the global object, but in order to create those, we need the
1354  // native context).
1355  native_context_ = factory()->NewNativeContext();
1356 
1357  AddToWeakNativeContextList(isolate(), *native_context());
1358  isolate()->set_context(*native_context());
1359 }

1361 void Genesis::InstallGlobalThisBinding() {
1362  DirectHandle<ScopeInfo> scope_info =
1363  isolate()->factory()->global_this_binding_scope_info();
1364  DirectHandle<Context> context =
1365  factory()->NewScriptContext(native_context(), scope_info);
1366 
1367  // Go ahead and hook it up while we're at it.
1368  int slot = scope_info->ReceiverContextSlotIndex();
1369  context->SetNoCell(slot, native_context()->global_proxy());
1370 
1371  Handle<ScriptContextTable> script_contexts(
1372  native_context()->script_context_table(), isolate());
1373  DirectHandle<ScriptContextTable> new_script_contexts =
1374  ScriptContextTable::Add(isolate(), script_contexts, context, false);
1375  native_context()->set_script_context_table(*new_script_contexts);

1377 
1378 DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> Genesis::CreateNewGlobals(
1379  v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
1380  DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy) {
1381  // The argument global_proxy_template aka data is an ObjectTemplateInfo.
1382  // It has a constructor pointer that points at global_constructor which is a
1383  // FunctionTemplateInfo.
1384  // The global_proxy_constructor is used to (re)initialize the
1385  // global_proxy. The global_proxy_constructor also has a prototype_template
1386  // pointer that points at js_global_object_template which is an
1387  // ObjectTemplateInfo.
1388  // That in turn has a constructor pointer that points at
1389  // js_global_object_constructor which is a FunctionTemplateInfo.
1390  // js_global_object_constructor is used to make js_global_object_function
1391  // js_global_object_function is used to make the new global_object.
1392  //
1393  // --- G l o b a l ---
1394  // Step 1: Create a fresh JSGlobalObject.
1395  DirectHandle<JSFunction> js_global_object_function;
1396  DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> js_global_object_template;
1397  if (!global_proxy_template.IsEmpty()) {
1398  // Get prototype template of the global_proxy_template.
1399  DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> data =
1400  v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global_proxy_template);
1401  DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> global_constructor(
1402  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(data->constructor()), isolate());
1403  DirectHandle<Object> proto_template(
1404  global_constructor->GetPrototypeTemplate(), isolate());
1405  if (!IsUndefined(*proto_template, isolate())) {
1406  js_global_object_template = Cast<ObjectTemplateInfo>(proto_template);
1407  }
1408  }
1409 
1410  if (js_global_object_template.is_null()) {
1411  DirectHandle<String> name = factory()->empty_string();
1412  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype =
1413  factory()->NewFunctionPrototype(isolate()->object_function());
1414  js_global_object_function = CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithPrototype(
1415  isolate(), name, Builtin::kIllegal, prototype, JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE,
1416  JSGlobalObject::kHeaderSize, 0, MUTABLE, 0, kDontAdapt);
1417 #ifdef DEBUG
1418  LookupIterator it(isolate(), prototype, factory()->constructor_string(),
1419  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
1420  DirectHandle<Object> value = Object::GetProperty(&it).ToHandleChecked();
1421  DCHECK(it.IsFound());
1422  DCHECK_EQ(*isolate()->object_function(), *value);
1423 #endif
1424  } else {
1425  DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> js_global_object_constructor(
1426  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(js_global_object_template->constructor()),
1427  isolate());
1428  js_global_object_function = ApiNatives::CreateApiFunction(
1429  isolate(), isolate()->native_context(), js_global_object_constructor,
1430  factory()->the_hole_value(), JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE);
1431  }
1432 
1433  js_global_object_function->initial_map()->set_is_prototype_map(true);
1434  js_global_object_function->initial_map()->set_is_dictionary_map(true);
1435  js_global_object_function->initial_map()->set_may_have_interesting_properties(
1436  true);
1437  DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object =
1438  factory()->NewJSGlobalObject(js_global_object_function);
1439 
1440  // Step 2: (re)initialize the global proxy object.
1441  DirectHandle<JSFunction> global_proxy_function;
1442  if (global_proxy_template.IsEmpty()) {
1443  DirectHandle<String> name = factory()->empty_string();
1444  global_proxy_function = CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithPrototype(
1445  isolate(), name, Builtin::kIllegal, factory()->the_hole_value(),
1446  JS_GLOBAL_PROXY_TYPE, JSGlobalProxy::SizeWithEmbedderFields(0), 0,
1447  MUTABLE, 0, kDontAdapt);
1448  } else {
1449  DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> data =
1450  v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global_proxy_template);
1451  DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> global_constructor(
1452  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(data->constructor()), isolate());
1453  global_proxy_function = ApiNatives::CreateApiFunction(
1454  isolate(), isolate()->native_context(), global_constructor,
1455  factory()->the_hole_value(), JS_GLOBAL_PROXY_TYPE);
1456  }
1457  global_proxy_function->initial_map()->set_is_access_check_needed(true);
1458  global_proxy_function->initial_map()->set_may_have_interesting_properties(
1459  true);
1460  native_context()->set_global_proxy_function(*global_proxy_function);
1461 
1462  // Set the global object as the (hidden) __proto__ of the global proxy after
1463  // ConfigureGlobalObject
1464  factory()->ReinitializeJSGlobalProxy(global_proxy, global_proxy_function);
1465 
1466  // Set up the pointer back from the global object to the global proxy.
1467  global_object->set_global_proxy(*global_proxy);
1468  // Set the native context of the global proxy.
1469  global_proxy->map()->set_map(isolate(), native_context()->meta_map());
1470  // Set the global proxy of the native context. If the native context has been
1471  // deserialized, the global proxy is already correctly set up by the
1472  // deserializer. Otherwise it's undefined.
1473  DCHECK(IsUndefined(native_context()->GetNoCell(Context::GLOBAL_PROXY_INDEX),
1474  isolate()) ||
1475  native_context()->global_proxy_object() == *global_proxy);
1476  native_context()->set_global_proxy_object(*global_proxy);
1477 
1478  return global_object;
1479 }
1480 
1481 void Genesis::HookUpGlobalProxy(DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy) {
1482  // Re-initialize the global proxy with the global proxy function from the
1483  // snapshot, and then set up the link to the native context.
1484  DirectHandle<JSFunction> global_proxy_function(
1485  native_context()->global_proxy_function(), isolate());
1486  factory()->ReinitializeJSGlobalProxy(global_proxy, global_proxy_function);
1487  DirectHandle<JSObject> global_object(
1488  Cast<JSObject>(native_context()->global_object()), isolate());
1489  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), global_proxy, global_object);
1490  global_proxy->map()->set_map(isolate(), native_context()->meta_map());
1491  DCHECK(native_context()->global_proxy() == *global_proxy);
1492 }
1493 
1494 void Genesis::HookUpGlobalObject(DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object) {
1495  DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object_from_snapshot(
1496  Cast<JSGlobalObject>(native_context()->extension()), isolate());
1497  native_context()->set_extension(*global_object);
1498  native_context()->set_security_token(*global_object);
1499 
1500  TransferNamedProperties(global_object_from_snapshot, global_object);
1501  if (global_object_from_snapshot->HasDictionaryElements()) {
1502  JSObject::NormalizeElements(isolate(), global_object);
1503  }
1504  DCHECK_EQ(global_object_from_snapshot->GetElementsKind(),
1505  global_object->GetElementsKind());
1506  TransferIndexedProperties(global_object_from_snapshot, global_object);
1507 }
1508 
1509 // See https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-ordinarycreatefromconstructor for details
1510 // about intrinsicDefaultProto concept. In short it's about using proper
1511 // prototype object from constructor's realm when the constructor has
1512 // non-instance prototype.
1513 static void InstallWithIntrinsicDefaultProto(Isolate* isolate,
1514  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
1515  int context_index) {
1516  DirectHandle<Smi> index(Smi::FromInt(context_index), isolate);
1517  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, function,
1518  isolate->factory()->native_context_index_symbol(),
1519  index, NONE);
1520  isolate->native_context()->set(context_index, *function, UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER,
1521  kReleaseStore);
1522 }
1523 
1524 void InstallError(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> global,
1525  DirectHandle<String> name, int context_index,
1526  Builtin error_constructor, int error_function_length) {
1527  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
1528 
1529  // Most Error objects consist of a message, a stack trace, and possibly a
1530  // cause. Reserve three in-object properties for these.
1531  const int in_object_properties = 3;
1532  const int kErrorObjectSize =
1533  JSObject::kHeaderSize + in_object_properties * kTaggedSize;
1534  DirectHandle<JSFunction> error_fun =
1535  InstallFunction(isolate, global, name, JS_ERROR_TYPE, kErrorObjectSize,
1536  in_object_properties, factory->the_hole_value(),
1537  error_constructor, error_function_length, kDontAdapt);
1538 
1539  if (context_index == Context::ERROR_FUNCTION_INDEX) {
1540  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate, error_fun, "captureStackTrace",
1541  Builtin::kErrorCaptureStackTrace, 2, kDontAdapt);
1542  }
1543 
1544  InstallWithIntrinsicDefaultProto(isolate, error_fun, context_index);
1545 
1546  {
1547  // Setup %XXXErrorPrototype%.
1548  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype(
1549  Cast<JSObject>(error_fun->instance_prototype()), isolate);
1550 
1551  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, prototype, factory->name_string(), name,
1552  DONT_ENUM);
1553  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, prototype, factory->message_string(),
1554  factory->empty_string(), DONT_ENUM);
1555 
1556  if (context_index == Context::ERROR_FUNCTION_INDEX) {
1557  DirectHandle<JSFunction> to_string_fun =
1558  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate, prototype, "toString",
1559  Builtin::kErrorPrototypeToString, 0, kAdapt);
1560  isolate->native_context()->set_error_to_string(*to_string_fun);
1561  isolate->native_context()->set_initial_error_prototype(*prototype);
1562  } else {
1563  DirectHandle<JSFunction> global_error = isolate->error_function();
1564  CHECK(JSReceiver::SetPrototype(isolate, error_fun, global_error, false,
1565  kThrowOnError)
1566  .FromMaybe(false));
1567  CHECK(JSReceiver::SetPrototype(
1568  isolate, prototype,
1569  direct_handle(global_error->prototype(), isolate), false,
1570  kThrowOnError)
1571  .FromMaybe(false));
1572  }
1573  }
1574 
1575  DirectHandle<Map> initial_map(error_fun->initial_map(), isolate);
1576  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate, initial_map, 3);
1577  const int kJSErrorErrorStackSymbolIndex = 0;
1578  const int kJSErrorErrorMessageSymbolIndex = 1;
1579 
1580  { // error_stack_symbol
1581  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate, factory->error_stack_symbol(),
1582  kJSErrorErrorStackSymbolIndex,
1583  DONT_ENUM, Representation::Tagged());
1584  initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate, &d);
1585  }
1586  {
1587  // error_message_symbol
1588  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
1589  isolate, factory->error_message_symbol(),
1590  kJSErrorErrorMessageSymbolIndex, DONT_ENUM, Representation::Tagged());
1591  initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate, &d);
1592  }
1593  { // stack
1594  DirectHandle<AccessorPair> new_pair = factory->NewAccessorPair();
1595  new_pair->set_getter(*factory->error_stack_getter_fun_template());
1596  new_pair->set_setter(*factory->error_stack_setter_fun_template());
1597 
1598  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(factory->stack_string(),
1599  new_pair, DONT_ENUM);
1600  initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate, &d);
1601  }
1602 }

1604 #ifdef V8_TEMPORAL_SUPPORT
1605 
1606 namespace {
1607 
1608 Handle<JSObject> InitializeTemporal(Isolate* isolate) {
1609  DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context = isolate->native_context();
1610 
1611  // Already initialized?
1612  Handle<HeapObject> maybe_temporal(native_context->temporal_object(), isolate);
1613  if (IsJSObject(*maybe_temporal)) {
1614  return Cast<JSObject>(maybe_temporal);
1615  }
1616 
1617  isolate->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kTemporalObject);
1618 
1619  // -- T e m p o r a l
1620  // #sec-temporal-objects
1621  Handle<JSObject> temporal = isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(
1622  isolate->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1623 
1624  // The initial value of the @@toStringTag property is the string value
1625  // *"Temporal"*.
1626  // https://github.com/tc39/proposal-temporal/issues/1539
1627  InstallToStringTag(isolate, temporal, "Temporal");
1628 
1629  { // -- N o w
1630  // #sec-temporal-now-object
1631  DirectHandle<JSObject> now = isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(
1632  isolate->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1633  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, temporal, "Now", now, DONT_ENUM);
1634  InstallToStringTag(isolate, now, "Temporal.Now");
1635 
1636  // Note: There are NO Temporal.Now.plainTime
1637  // See https://github.com/tc39/proposal-temporal/issues/1540
1638 #define NOW_LIST(V) \
1639  V(instant, Instant, 0) \
1640  V(plainDateTime, PlainDateTime, 1) \
1641  V(plainDateTimeISO, PlainDateTimeISO, 0) \
1642  V(zonedDateTime, ZonedDateTime, 1) \
1643  V(zonedDateTimeISO, ZonedDateTimeISO, 0) \
1644  V(plainDate, PlainDate, 1) \
1645  V(plainDateISO, PlainDateISO, 0) \
1646  V(plainTimeISO, PlainTimeISO, 0)
1647 
1648 #define INSTALL_NOW_FUNC(p, N, n) \
1649  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate, now, #p, Builtin::kTemporalNow##N, n, \
1650  kDontAdapt);
1651 
1652  NOW_LIST(INSTALL_NOW_FUNC)
1653 #undef INSTALL_NOW_FUNC
1654 #undef NOW_LIST
1655  }
1656 #define INSTALL_TEMPORAL_CTOR_AND_PROTOTYPE(N, U, NUM_ARGS) \
1657  DirectHandle<JSFunction> obj_func = InstallFunction( \
1658  isolate, temporal, #N, JS_TEMPORAL_##U##_TYPE, \
1659  JSTemporal##N::kHeaderSize, 0, isolate->factory()->the_hole_value(), \
1660  Builtin::kTemporal##N##Constructor, NUM_ARGS, kDontAdapt); \
1661  InstallWithIntrinsicDefaultProto(isolate, obj_func, \
1662  Context::JS_TEMPORAL_##U##_FUNCTION_INDEX); \
1663  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype( \
1664  Cast<JSObject>(obj_func->instance_prototype()), isolate); \
1665  InstallToStringTag(isolate, prototype, "Temporal." #N);
1666 
1667 #define INSTALL_TEMPORAL_FUNC(T, name, N, arg) \
1668  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate, obj_func, #name, Builtin::kTemporal##T##N, \
1669  arg, kDontAdapt);

2120 void LazyInitializeDateToTemporalInstant(
2121  v8::Local<v8::Name> name, const v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2122  Isolate* isolate = reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
2123  InitializeTemporal(isolate);
2124  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = SimpleCreateFunction(
2125  isolate, isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String("toTemporalInstant"),
2126  Builtin::kDatePrototypeToTemporalInstant, 0, kDontAdapt);
2127  info.GetReturnValue().Set(v8::Utils::ToLocal(function));
2128 }
2129 
2130 void LazyInitializeGlobalThisTemporal(
2131  v8::Local<v8::Name> name, const v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2132  Isolate* isolate = reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
2133  DirectHandle<JSObject> temporal = InitializeTemporal(isolate);
2134  info.GetReturnValue().Set(v8::Utils::ToLocal(temporal));
2135 }

2140 
2141 // This is only called if we are not using snapshots. The equivalent
2142 // work in the snapshot case is done in HookUpGlobalObject.
2143 void Genesis::InitializeGlobal(DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object,
2144  DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function) {
2145  // --- N a t i v e C o n t e x t ---
2146  // Set extension and global object.
2147  native_context()->set_extension(*global_object);
2148  // Security setup: Set the security token of the native context to the global
2149  // object. This makes the security check between two different contexts fail
2150  // by default even in case of global object reinitialization.
2151  native_context()->set_security_token(*global_object);
2152 
2153  Factory* factory = isolate_->factory();
2154 
2155  { // -- C o n t e x t

4025  {
4026  // Set up the maps for SegmentDataObjects, with and without "isWordLike"
4027  // property.
4028  constexpr int kNumProperties = 3;
4029  constexpr int kNumPropertiesWithWordlike = kNumProperties + 1;
4030  constexpr int kInstanceSize =
4031  JSObject::kHeaderSize + kNumProperties * kTaggedSize;
4032  constexpr int kInstanceSizeWithWordlike =
4033  JSObject::kHeaderSize + kNumPropertiesWithWordlike * kTaggedSize;
4034  DirectHandle<Map> map = factory->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
4035  JS_OBJECT_TYPE, kInstanceSize, TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND,
4036  kNumProperties);
4037  DirectHandle<Map> map_with_wordlike =
4038  factory->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
4039  JS_OBJECT_TYPE, kInstanceSizeWithWordlike,
4040  TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, kNumPropertiesWithWordlike);
4041  map->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
4042  map_with_wordlike->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
4043  map->set_prototype(*isolate_->initial_object_prototype());
4044  map_with_wordlike->set_prototype(*isolate_->initial_object_prototype());
4045  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate_, map, kNumProperties);
4046  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate_, map_with_wordlike,
4047  kNumPropertiesWithWordlike);
4048  int index = 0;
4049  { // segment
4050  Descriptor d =
4051  Descriptor::DataField(isolate_, factory->segment_string(),
4052  index++, NONE, Representation::Tagged());
4053  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4054  map_with_wordlike->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4055  }
4056  { // index
4057  Descriptor d =
4058  Descriptor::DataField(isolate_, factory->index_string(), index++,
4059  NONE, Representation::Tagged());
4060  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4061  map_with_wordlike->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4062  }
4063  { // input
4064  Descriptor d =
4065  Descriptor::DataField(isolate_, factory->input_string(), index++,
4066  NONE, Representation::Tagged());
4067  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4068  map_with_wordlike->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4069  }
4070  DCHECK_EQ(index, kNumProperties);
4071  { // isWordLike
4072  Descriptor d =
4073  Descriptor::DataField(isolate_, factory->isWordLike_string(),
4074  index++, NONE, Representation::Tagged());
4075  map_with_wordlike->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4076  }
4077  DCHECK_EQ(index, kNumPropertiesWithWordlike);
4078  DCHECK(!map->is_dictionary_map());
4079  DCHECK(!map_with_wordlike->is_dictionary_map());
4080  native_context()->set_intl_segment_data_object_map(*map);
4081  native_context()->set_intl_segment_data_object_wordlike_map(
4082  *map_with_wordlike);
4083  }
4084  }

4118  { // -- A r r a y B u f f e r
4119  DirectHandle<String> name = factory->ArrayBuffer_string();

5046 
5047 DirectHandle<JSFunction> Genesis::InstallTypedArray(
5048  const char* name, ElementsKind elements_kind, InstanceType constructor_type,
5049  int rab_gsab_initial_map_index) {
5050  DirectHandle<JSObject> global(native_context()->global_object(), isolate());
5051 
5052  DirectHandle<JSObject> typed_array_prototype =
5053  isolate()->typed_array_prototype();
5054  DirectHandle<JSFunction> typed_array_function =
5055  isolate()->typed_array_function();
5056 
5057  DirectHandle<JSFunction> result = InstallFunction(
5058  isolate(), global, name, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE,
5059  JSTypedArray::kSizeWithEmbedderFields, 0, factory()->the_hole_value(),
5060  Builtin::kTypedArrayConstructor, 3, kDontAdapt);
5061  result->initial_map()->set_elements_kind(elements_kind);
5062 
5063  CHECK(JSObject::SetPrototype(isolate(), result, typed_array_function, false,
5064  kDontThrow)
5065  .FromJust());
5066 
5067  DirectHandle<Smi> bytes_per_element(
5068  Smi::FromInt(1 << ElementsKindToShiftSize(elements_kind)), isolate());
5069 
5070  InstallConstant(isolate(), result, "BYTES_PER_ELEMENT", bytes_per_element);
5071 
5072  // TODO(v8:11256, ishell): given the granularity of typed array constructor
5073  // protectors, consider creating only one constructor instance type for all
5074  // typed array constructors.
5075  SetConstructorInstanceType(isolate_, result, constructor_type);
5076 
5077  // Setup prototype object.
5078  DCHECK(IsJSObject(result->prototype()));
5079  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype(Cast<JSObject>(result->prototype()),
5080  isolate());
5081 
5082  CHECK(JSObject::SetPrototype(isolate(), prototype, typed_array_prototype,
5083  false, kDontThrow)
5084  .FromJust());
5085 
5086  CHECK_NE(prototype->map().ptr(),
5087  isolate_->initial_object_prototype()->map().ptr());
5088  prototype->map()->set_instance_type(JS_TYPED_ARRAY_PROTOTYPE_TYPE);
5089 
5090  InstallConstant(isolate(), prototype, "BYTES_PER_ELEMENT", bytes_per_element);
5091 
5092  // RAB / GSAB backed TypedArrays don't have separate constructors, but they
5093  // have their own maps. Create the corresponding map here.
5094  DirectHandle<Map> rab_gsab_initial_map =
5095  factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
5096  JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE, JSTypedArray::kSizeWithEmbedderFields,
5097  GetCorrespondingRabGsabElementsKind(elements_kind), 0);
5098  rab_gsab_initial_map->SetConstructor(*result);
5099 
5100  if (rab_gsab_initial_map_index == Context::RAB_GSAB_FLOAT16_ARRAY_MAP_INDEX &&
5101  v8_flags.js_float16array) {
5102  LOG(isolate(), MapDetails(*rab_gsab_initial_map));
5103  }
5104 
5105  native_context()->set(rab_gsab_initial_map_index, *rab_gsab_initial_map,
5106  UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER, kReleaseStore);
5107  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), rab_gsab_initial_map, prototype);
5108 
5109  return result;
5110 }
5111 
5112 void Genesis::InitializeExperimentalGlobal() {
5113 #define FEATURE_INITIALIZE_GLOBAL(id, descr) InitializeGlobal_##id();
5114 
5115  // Initialize features from more mature to less mature, because less mature
5116  // features may depend on more mature features having been initialized
5117  // already.
5118  HARMONY_SHIPPING(FEATURE_INITIALIZE_GLOBAL)
5119  JAVASCRIPT_SHIPPING_FEATURES(FEATURE_INITIALIZE_GLOBAL)
5120  HARMONY_STAGED(FEATURE_INITIALIZE_GLOBAL)
5121  JAVASCRIPT_STAGED_FEATURES(FEATURE_INITIALIZE_GLOBAL)
5122  HARMONY_INPROGRESS(FEATURE_INITIALIZE_GLOBAL)
5123  JAVASCRIPT_INPROGRESS_FEATURES(FEATURE_INITIALIZE_GLOBAL)
5124 #undef FEATURE_INITIALIZE_GLOBAL
5125  InitializeGlobal_regexp_linear_flag();
5126  InitializeGlobal_sharedarraybuffer();
5127 }

5129 namespace {
5130 class TryCallScope {
5131  public:
5132  explicit TryCallScope(Isolate* isolate) : top(isolate->thread_local_top()) {
5133  top->IncrementCallDepth<true>(this);
5134  }
5135  ~TryCallScope() { top->DecrementCallDepth(this); }
5136 
5137  private:
5138  friend class i::ThreadLocalTop;
5139  ThreadLocalTop* top;
5140  Address previous_stack_height_;
5141 };
5142 } // namespace
5143 
5144 bool Genesis::CompileExtension(Isolate* isolate, v8::Extension* extension) {
5145  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
5146  HandleScope scope(isolate);
5147  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> function_info;
5148 
5149  Handle<String> source =
5150  isolate->factory()
5151  ->NewExternalStringFromOneByte(extension->source())
5152  .ToHandleChecked();
5153  DCHECK(source->IsOneByteRepresentation());
5154 
5155  // If we can't find the function in the cache, we compile a new
5156  // function and insert it into the cache.
5157  base::Vector<const char> name = base::CStrVector(extension->name());
5158  SourceCodeCache* cache = isolate->bootstrapper()->extensions_cache();
5159  DirectHandle<Context> context(isolate->context(), isolate);
5160  DCHECK(IsNativeContext(*context));
5161 
5162  if (!cache->Lookup(isolate, name, &function_info)) {
5163  Handle<String> script_name =
5164  factory->NewStringFromUtf8(name).ToHandleChecked();
5165  ScriptCompiler::CompilationDetails compilation_details;
5166  MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_function_info =
5167  Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForScriptWithExtension(
5168  isolate, source, ScriptDetails(script_name), extension,
5169  ScriptCompiler::kNoCompileOptions, EXTENSION_CODE,
5170  &compilation_details);
5171  if (!maybe_function_info.ToHandle(&function_info)) return false;
5172  cache->Add(isolate, name, function_info);
5173  }
5174 
5175  // Set up the function context. Conceptually, we should clone the
5176  // function before overwriting the context but since we're in a
5177  // single-threaded environment it is not strictly necessary.
5178  DirectHandle<JSFunction> fun =
5179  Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, function_info, context}.Build();
5180 
5181  // Call function using either the runtime object or the global
5182  // object as the receiver. Provide no parameters.
5183  DirectHandle<Object> receiver = isolate->global_object();
5184  DirectHandle<FixedArray> host_defined_options =
5185  isolate->factory()->empty_fixed_array();
5186  TryCallScope try_call_scope(isolate);
5187  // Blink generally assumes that context creation (where extension compilation
5188  // is part) cannot be interrupted.
5189  PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
5190  return !Execution::TryCallScript(isolate, fun, receiver, host_defined_options)
5191  .is_null();
5192 }
