5194 void Genesis::InitializeIteratorFunctions() {
5195  Isolate* isolate = isolate_;
5196  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
5197  HandleScope scope(isolate);
5198  DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context = isolate->native_context();
5199  DirectHandle<JSObject> iterator_prototype(
5200  native_context->initial_iterator_prototype(), isolate);
5201 
5202  { // -- G e n e r a t o r
5203  PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, native_context->generator_function_map());
5204  DirectHandle<JSObject> generator_function_prototype(
5205  iter.GetCurrent<JSObject>(), isolate);
5206  DirectHandle<JSFunction> generator_function_function = CreateFunction(
5207  isolate, "GeneratorFunction", JS_FUNCTION_TYPE,
5208  JSFunction::kSizeWithPrototype, 0, generator_function_prototype,
5209  Builtin::kGeneratorFunctionConstructor, 1, kDontAdapt);
5210  generator_function_function->set_prototype_or_initial_map(
5211  native_context->generator_function_map(), kReleaseStore);
5212  InstallWithIntrinsicDefaultProto(
5213  isolate, generator_function_function,
5214  Context::GENERATOR_FUNCTION_FUNCTION_INDEX);
5215 
5216  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate, generator_function_function,
5217  isolate->function_function());
5218  JSObject::AddProperty(
5219  isolate, generator_function_prototype, factory->constructor_string(),
5220  generator_function_function,
5221  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY));
5222 
5223  native_context->generator_function_map()->SetConstructor(
5224  *generator_function_function);
5225  native_context->generator_function_with_name_map()->SetConstructor(
5226  *generator_function_function);
5227  }
5228 
5229  { // -- A s y n c G e n e r a t o r
5230  PrototypeIterator iter(isolate,
5231  native_context->async_generator_function_map());
5232  DirectHandle<JSObject> async_generator_function_prototype(
5233  iter.GetCurrent<JSObject>(), isolate);
5234 
5235  DirectHandle<JSFunction> async_generator_function_function = CreateFunction(
5236  isolate, "AsyncGeneratorFunction", JS_FUNCTION_TYPE,
5237  JSFunction::kSizeWithPrototype, 0, async_generator_function_prototype,
5238  Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorFunctionConstructor, 1, kDontAdapt);
5239  async_generator_function_function->set_prototype_or_initial_map(
5240  native_context->async_generator_function_map(), kReleaseStore);
5241  InstallWithIntrinsicDefaultProto(
5242  isolate, async_generator_function_function,
5243  Context::ASYNC_GENERATOR_FUNCTION_FUNCTION_INDEX);
5244 
5245  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate, async_generator_function_function,
5246  isolate->function_function());
5247 
5248  JSObject::AddProperty(
5249  isolate, async_generator_function_prototype,
5250  factory->constructor_string(), async_generator_function_function,
5251  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY));
5252 
5253  native_context->async_generator_function_map()->SetConstructor(
5254  *async_generator_function_function);
5255  native_context->async_generator_function_with_name_map()->SetConstructor(
5256  *async_generator_function_function);
5257  }
5258 
5259  { // -- S e t I t e r a t o r
5260  // Setup %SetIteratorPrototype%.
5261  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype =
5262  factory->NewJSObject(isolate->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
5263  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate, prototype, iterator_prototype);
5264 
5265  InstallToStringTag(isolate, prototype, factory->SetIterator_string());
5266 
5267  // Install the next function on the {prototype}.
5268  InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate, prototype, "next",
5269  Builtin::kSetIteratorPrototypeNext, 0, kAdapt);
5270  native_context->set_initial_set_iterator_prototype(*prototype);
5271  CHECK_NE(prototype->map().ptr(),
5272  isolate_->initial_object_prototype()->map().ptr());
5273  prototype->map()->set_instance_type(JS_SET_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE);
5274 
5275  // Setup SetIterator constructor.
5276  DirectHandle<JSFunction> set_iterator_function =
5277  CreateFunction(isolate, "SetIterator", JS_SET_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE,
5278  JSSetIterator::kHeaderSize, 0, prototype,
5279  Builtin::kIllegal, 0, kDontAdapt);
5280  set_iterator_function->shared()->set_native(false);
5281 
5282  DirectHandle<Map> set_value_iterator_map(
5283  set_iterator_function->initial_map(), isolate);
5284  native_context->set_set_value_iterator_map(*set_value_iterator_map);
5285 
5286  DirectHandle<Map> set_key_value_iterator_map = Map::Copy(
5287  isolate, set_value_iterator_map, "JS_SET_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE");
5288  set_key_value_iterator_map->set_instance_type(
5289  JS_SET_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE);
5290  native_context->set_set_key_value_iterator_map(*set_key_value_iterator_map);
5291  }
5292 
5293  { // -- M a p I t e r a t o r
5294  // Setup %MapIteratorPrototype%.
5295  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype =
5296  factory->NewJSObject(isolate->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
5297  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate, prototype, iterator_prototype);
5298 
5299  InstallToStringTag(isolate, prototype, factory->MapIterator_string());
5300 
5301  // Install the next function on the {prototype}.
5302  InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate, prototype, "next",
5303  Builtin::kMapIteratorPrototypeNext, 0, kAdapt);
5304  native_context->set_initial_map_iterator_prototype(*prototype);
5305  CHECK_NE(prototype->map().ptr(),
5306  isolate_->initial_object_prototype()->map().ptr());
5307  prototype->map()->set_instance_type(JS_MAP_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE);
5308 
5309  // Setup MapIterator constructor.
5310  DirectHandle<JSFunction> map_iterator_function =
5311  CreateFunction(isolate, "MapIterator", JS_MAP_KEY_ITERATOR_TYPE,
5312  JSMapIterator::kHeaderSize, 0, prototype,
5313  Builtin::kIllegal, 0, kDontAdapt);
5314  map_iterator_function->shared()->set_native(false);
5315 
5316  DirectHandle<Map> map_key_iterator_map(map_iterator_function->initial_map(),
5317  isolate);
5318  native_context->set_map_key_iterator_map(*map_key_iterator_map);
5319 
5320  DirectHandle<Map> map_key_value_iterator_map = Map::Copy(
5321  isolate, map_key_iterator_map, "JS_MAP_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE");
5322  map_key_value_iterator_map->set_instance_type(
5323  JS_MAP_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE);
5324  native_context->set_map_key_value_iterator_map(*map_key_value_iterator_map);
5325 
5326  DirectHandle<Map> map_value_iterator_map =
5327  Map::Copy(isolate, map_key_iterator_map, "JS_MAP_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE");
5328  map_value_iterator_map->set_instance_type(JS_MAP_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE);
5329  native_context->set_map_value_iterator_map(*map_value_iterator_map);
5330  }
5331 
5332  { // -- A s y n c F u n c t i o n
5333  // Builtin functions for AsyncFunction.
5334  PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, native_context->async_function_map());
5335  DirectHandle<JSObject> async_function_prototype(iter.GetCurrent<JSObject>(),
5336  isolate);
5337 
5338  DirectHandle<JSFunction> async_function_constructor = CreateFunction(
5339  isolate, "AsyncFunction", JS_FUNCTION_TYPE,
5340  JSFunction::kSizeWithPrototype, 0, async_function_prototype,
5341  Builtin::kAsyncFunctionConstructor, 1, kDontAdapt);
5342  async_function_constructor->set_prototype_or_initial_map(
5343  native_context->async_function_map(), kReleaseStore);
5344  InstallWithIntrinsicDefaultProto(isolate, async_function_constructor,
5345  Context::ASYNC_FUNCTION_FUNCTION_INDEX);
5346 
5347  native_context->set_async_function_constructor(*async_function_constructor);
5348  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate, async_function_constructor,
5349  isolate->function_function());
5350 
5351  JSObject::AddProperty(
5352  isolate, async_function_prototype, factory->constructor_string(),
5353  async_function_constructor,
5354  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY));
5355 
5356  // Async functions don't have a prototype, but they use generator objects
5357  // under the hood to model the suspend/resume (in await). Instead of using
5358  // the "prototype" / initial_map machinery (like for (async) generators),
5359  // there's one global (per native context) map here that is used for the
5360  // async function generator objects. These objects never escape to user
5361  // JavaScript anyways.
5362  DirectHandle<Map> async_function_object_map =
5363  factory->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
5364  JS_ASYNC_FUNCTION_OBJECT_TYPE, JSAsyncFunctionObject::kHeaderSize);
5365  native_context->set_async_function_object_map(*async_function_object_map);
5366 
5367  isolate_->async_function_map()->SetConstructor(*async_function_constructor);
5368  isolate_->async_function_with_name_map()->SetConstructor(
5369  *async_function_constructor);
5370  }
5371 }

5373 void Genesis::InitializeCallSiteBuiltins() {
5374  Factory* factory = isolate()->factory();
5375  HandleScope scope(isolate());
5376  // -- C a l l S i t e
5377  // Builtin functions for CallSite.
5378 
5379  // CallSites are a special case; the constructor is for our private use
5380  // only, therefore we set it up as a builtin that throws. Internally, we use
5381  // CallSiteUtils::Construct to create CallSite objects.
5382 
5383  DirectHandle<JSFunction> callsite_fun = CreateFunction(
5384  isolate(), "CallSite", JS_OBJECT_TYPE, JSObject::kHeaderSize, 0,
5385  factory->the_hole_value(), Builtin::kUnsupportedThrower, 0, kDontAdapt);
5386  isolate()->native_context()->set_callsite_function(*callsite_fun);
5387 
5388  // Setup CallSite.prototype.
5389  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype(
5390  Cast<JSObject>(callsite_fun->instance_prototype()), isolate());
5391 
5392  struct FunctionInfo {
5393  const char* name;
5394  Builtin id;
5395  };
5396 
5397  FunctionInfo infos[] = {
5398  {"getColumnNumber", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetColumnNumber},
5399  {"getEnclosingColumnNumber",
5400  Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetEnclosingColumnNumber},
5401  {"getEnclosingLineNumber",
5402  Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetEnclosingLineNumber},
5403  {"getEvalOrigin", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetEvalOrigin},
5404  {"getFileName", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetFileName},
5405  {"getFunction", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetFunction},
5406  {"getFunctionName", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetFunctionName},
5407  {"getLineNumber", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetLineNumber},
5408  {"getMethodName", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetMethodName},
5409  {"getPosition", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetPosition},
5410  {"getPromiseIndex", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetPromiseIndex},
5411  {"getScriptNameOrSourceURL",
5412  Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetScriptNameOrSourceURL},
5413  {"getScriptHash", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetScriptHash},
5414  {"getThis", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetThis},
5415  {"getTypeName", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeGetTypeName},
5416  {"isAsync", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeIsAsync},
5417  {"isConstructor", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeIsConstructor},
5418  {"isEval", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeIsEval},
5419  {"isNative", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeIsNative},
5420  {"isPromiseAll", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeIsPromiseAll},
5421  {"isToplevel", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeIsToplevel},
5422  {"toString", Builtin::kCallSitePrototypeToString}};
5423 
5424  PropertyAttributes attrs =
5425  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY);
5426 
5427  for (const FunctionInfo& info : infos) {

5551 void Genesis::InitializeGlobal_harmony_shadow_realm() {
5552  if (!v8_flags.harmony_shadow_realm) return;
5553  Factory* factory = isolate()->factory();
5554  // -- S h a d o w R e a l m
5555  // #sec-shadowrealm-objects
5556  DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global(native_context()->global_object(),
5557  isolate());
5558  DirectHandle<JSFunction> shadow_realm_fun =
5559  InstallFunction(isolate_, global, "ShadowRealm", JS_SHADOW_REALM_TYPE,
5560  JSShadowRealm::kHeaderSize, 0, factory->the_hole_value(),
5561  Builtin::kShadowRealmConstructor, 0, kDontAdapt);
5562 
5563  // Setup %ShadowRealmPrototype%.
5564  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype(
5565  Cast<JSObject>(shadow_realm_fun->instance_prototype()), isolate());
5566 
5567  InstallToStringTag(isolate_, prototype, factory->ShadowRealm_string());
5568 
5569  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate_, prototype, "evaluate",
5570  Builtin::kShadowRealmPrototypeEvaluate, 1, kAdapt);
5571  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate_, prototype, "importValue",
5572  Builtin::kShadowRealmPrototypeImportValue, 2, kAdapt);
5573 
5574  { // --- W r a p p e d F u n c t i o n
5575  DirectHandle<Map> map = factory->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
5576  JS_WRAPPED_FUNCTION_TYPE, JSWrappedFunction::kHeaderSize,
5577  TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, 0);
5578  map->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
5579  map->set_is_callable(true);
5580  DirectHandle<JSObject> empty_function(
5581  native_context()->function_prototype(), isolate());
5582  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, empty_function);
5583 
5584  PropertyAttributes roc_attribs =
5585  static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY);
5586  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate_, map, 2);
5587  { // length
5588  static_assert(
5589  JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex ==
5590  0);
5591  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
5592  factory->length_string(), factory->wrapped_function_length_accessor(),
5593  roc_attribs);
5594  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
5595  }
5596 
5597  { // name
5598  static_assert(
5599  JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kNameDescriptorIndex ==
5600  1);
5601  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
5602  factory->name_string(), factory->wrapped_function_name_accessor(),
5603  roc_attribs);
5604  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
5605  }
5606 
5607  native_context()->set_wrapped_function_map(*map);
5608  }
5609 
5610  // Internal steps of ShadowRealmImportValue
5611  {
5612  DirectHandle<JSFunction> shadow_realm_import_value_rejected =
5613  SimpleCreateFunction(isolate(), factory->empty_string(),
5614  Builtin::kShadowRealmImportValueRejected, 1,
5615  kAdapt);
5616  shadow_realm_import_value_rejected->shared()->set_native(false);
5617  native_context()->set_shadow_realm_import_value_rejected(
5618  *shadow_realm_import_value_rejected);
5619  }
5620 }

5970 DirectHandle<JSFunction> Genesis::CreateArrayBuffer(
5971  DirectHandle<String> name, ArrayBufferKind array_buffer_kind) {
5972  // Create the %ArrayBufferPrototype%
5973  // Setup the {prototype} with the given {name} for @@toStringTag.
5974  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype = factory()->NewJSObject(
5975  isolate()->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
5976  InstallToStringTag(isolate(), prototype, name);
5977 
5978  // Allocate the constructor with the given {prototype}.
5979  DirectHandle<JSFunction> array_buffer_fun =
5980  CreateFunction(isolate(), name, JS_ARRAY_BUFFER_TYPE,
5981  JSArrayBuffer::kSizeWithEmbedderFields, 0, prototype,
5982  Builtin::kArrayBufferConstructor, 1, kAdapt);
5983 
5984  // Install the "constructor" property on the {prototype}.
5985  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), prototype, factory()->constructor_string(),
5986  array_buffer_fun, DONT_ENUM);
5987 
5988  switch (array_buffer_kind) {
5989  case ARRAY_BUFFER:
5990  InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), array_buffer_fun, "isView",
5991  Builtin::kArrayBufferIsView, 1, kAdapt);
5992 
5993  // Install the "byteLength" getter on the {prototype}.
5994  SimpleInstallGetter(isolate(), prototype, factory()->byte_length_string(),
5995  Builtin::kArrayBufferPrototypeGetByteLength, kAdapt);
5996  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), prototype, "slice",
5997  Builtin::kArrayBufferPrototypeSlice, 2, kAdapt);
5998  break;
5999 
6000  case SHARED_ARRAY_BUFFER:
6001  // Install the "byteLength" getter on the {prototype}.
6002  SimpleInstallGetter(isolate(), prototype, factory()->byte_length_string(),
6003  Builtin::kSharedArrayBufferPrototypeGetByteLength,
6004  kDontAdapt);
6005  SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), prototype, "slice",
6006  Builtin::kSharedArrayBufferPrototypeSlice, 2,
6007  kAdapt);
6008  break;
6009  }
6010 
6011  return array_buffer_fun;
6012 }
6013 
6014 // TODO(jgruber): Refactor this into some kind of meaningful organization. There
6015 // is likely no reason remaining for these objects to be installed here. For
6016 // example, global object setup done in this function could likely move to
6017 // InitializeGlobal.
6018 bool Genesis::InstallABunchOfRandomThings() {
6019  HandleScope scope(isolate());
6020 
6021  auto fast_template_instantiations_cache =
6022  isolate()->factory()->NewFixedArrayWithHoles(
6023  TemplateInfo::kFastTemplateInstantiationsCacheSize);
6024  native_context()->set_fast_template_instantiations_cache(
6025  *fast_template_instantiations_cache);
6026 
6027  auto slow_template_instantiations_cache =
6028  EphemeronHashTable::New(isolate(), ApiNatives::kInitialFunctionCacheSize);
6029  native_context()->set_slow_template_instantiations_cache(
6030  *slow_template_instantiations_cache);
6031 
6032  auto wasm_debug_maps = isolate()->factory()->empty_fixed_array();
6033  native_context()->set_wasm_debug_maps(*wasm_debug_maps);
6034 
6035  // Store the map for the %ObjectPrototype% after the natives has been compiled
6036  // and the Object function has been set up.
6037  {
6038  DirectHandle<JSFunction> object_function(
6039  native_context()->object_function(), isolate());
6040  DCHECK(Cast<JSObject>(object_function->initial_map()->prototype())
6041  ->HasFastProperties());
6042  native_context()->set_object_function_prototype(
6043  Cast<JSObject>(object_function->initial_map()->prototype()));
6044  native_context()->set_object_function_prototype_map(
6045  Cast<HeapObject>(object_function->initial_map()->prototype())->map());
6046  }
6047 
6048  // Store the map for the %StringPrototype% after the natives has been compiled
6049  // and the String function has been set up.
6050  DirectHandle<JSFunction> string_function(native_context()->string_function(),
6051  isolate());
6052  Tagged<JSObject> string_function_prototype =
6053  Cast<JSObject>(string_function->initial_map()->prototype());
6054  DCHECK(string_function_prototype->HasFastProperties());
6055  native_context()->set_string_function_prototype_map(
6056  string_function_prototype->map());
6057 
6058  DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object(native_context()->global_object(),
6059  isolate());
6060 
6061  // Install Global.decodeURI.
6062  InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "decodeURI",
6063  Builtin::kGlobalDecodeURI, 1, kDontAdapt);
6064 
6065  // Install Global.decodeURIComponent.
6066  InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "decodeURIComponent",
6067  Builtin::kGlobalDecodeURIComponent, 1,
6068  kDontAdapt);
6069 
6070  // Install Global.encodeURI.
6071  InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "encodeURI",
6072  Builtin::kGlobalEncodeURI, 1, kDontAdapt);
6073 
6074  // Install Global.encodeURIComponent.
6075  InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "encodeURIComponent",
6076  Builtin::kGlobalEncodeURIComponent, 1,
6077  kDontAdapt);
6078 
6079  // Install Global.escape.
6080  InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "escape",
6081  Builtin::kGlobalEscape, 1, kDontAdapt);
6082 
6083  // Install Global.unescape.
6084  InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "unescape",
6085  Builtin::kGlobalUnescape, 1, kDontAdapt);
6086 
6087  // Install Global.eval.
6088  {
6089  DirectHandle<JSFunction> eval = SimpleInstallFunction(
6090  isolate(), global_object, "eval", Builtin::kGlobalEval, 1, kDontAdapt);
6091  native_context()->set_global_eval_fun(*eval);
6092  }
6093 
6094  // Install Global.isFinite
6095  InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "isFinite",
6096  Builtin::kGlobalIsFinite, 1, kAdapt);
6097 
6098  // Install Global.isNaN
6099  InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "isNaN",
6100  Builtin::kGlobalIsNaN, 1, kAdapt);
6101 
6102  // Install Array builtin functions.
6103  {
6104  DirectHandle<JSFunction> array_constructor(
6105  native_context()->array_function(), isolate());
6106  DirectHandle<JSArray> proto(Cast<JSArray>(array_constructor->prototype()),
6107  isolate());
6108 
6109  // Verification of important array prototype properties.
6110  Tagged<Object> length = proto->length();
6111  CHECK(IsSmi(length));
6112  CHECK_EQ(Smi::ToInt(length), 0);
6113  CHECK(proto->HasSmiOrObjectElements());
6114  // This is necessary to enable fast checks for absence of elements
6115  // on Array.prototype and below.
6116  proto->set_elements(ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).empty_fixed_array());
6117  }
6118 
6119  // Create a map for accessor property descriptors (a variant of JSObject
6120  // that predefines four properties get, set, configurable and enumerable).
6121  {
6122  // AccessorPropertyDescriptor initial map.
6123  DirectHandle<Map> map = factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
6124  JS_OBJECT_TYPE, JSAccessorPropertyDescriptor::kSize,
6125  TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, 4);
6126  // Create the descriptor array for the property descriptor object.
6127  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 4);
6128 
6129  { // get
6130  Descriptor d =
6131  Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->get_string(),
6132  JSAccessorPropertyDescriptor::kGetIndex, NONE,
6133  Representation::Tagged());
6134  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6135  }
6136  { // set
6137  Descriptor d =
6138  Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->set_string(),
6139  JSAccessorPropertyDescriptor::kSetIndex, NONE,
6140  Representation::Tagged());
6141  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6142  }
6143  { // enumerable
6144  Descriptor d =
6145  Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->enumerable_string(),
6146  JSAccessorPropertyDescriptor::kEnumerableIndex,
6147  NONE, Representation::Tagged());
6148  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6149  }
6150  { // configurable
6151  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6152  isolate(), factory()->configurable_string(),
6153  JSAccessorPropertyDescriptor::kConfigurableIndex, NONE,
6154  Representation::Tagged());
6155  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6156  }
6157 
6158  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, isolate()->initial_object_prototype());
6159  map->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
6160 
6161  native_context()->set_accessor_property_descriptor_map(*map);
6162  }
6163 
6164  // Create a map for data property descriptors (a variant of JSObject
6165  // that predefines four properties value, writable, configurable and
6166  // enumerable).
6167  {
6168  // DataPropertyDescriptor initial map.
6169  DirectHandle<Map> map = factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
6170  JS_OBJECT_TYPE, JSDataPropertyDescriptor::kSize,
6171  TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, 4);
6172  // Create the descriptor array for the property descriptor object.
6173  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 4);
6174 
6175  { // value
6176  Descriptor d =
6177  Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->value_string(),
6178  JSDataPropertyDescriptor::kValueIndex, NONE,
6179  Representation::Tagged());
6180  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6181  }
6182  { // writable
6183  Descriptor d =
6184  Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->writable_string(),
6185  JSDataPropertyDescriptor::kWritableIndex, NONE,
6186  Representation::Tagged());
6187  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6188  }
6189  { // enumerable
6190  Descriptor d =
6191  Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->enumerable_string(),
6192  JSDataPropertyDescriptor::kEnumerableIndex,
6193  NONE, Representation::Tagged());
6194  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6195  }
6196  { // configurable
6197  Descriptor d =
6198  Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->configurable_string(),
6199  JSDataPropertyDescriptor::kConfigurableIndex,
6200  NONE, Representation::Tagged());
6201  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6202  }
6203 
6204  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, isolate()->initial_object_prototype());
6205  map->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
6206 
6207  native_context()->set_data_property_descriptor_map(*map);
6208  }
6209 
6210  {
6211  // -- TemplateLiteral JSArray Map
6212  DirectHandle<JSFunction> array_function(native_context()->array_function(),
6213  isolate());
6214  DirectHandle<Map> template_map(array_function->initial_map(), isolate_);
6215  template_map = Map::CopyAsElementsKind(isolate_, template_map,
6216  PACKED_ELEMENTS, OMIT_TRANSITION);
6217  DCHECK_GE(TemplateLiteralObject::kHeaderSize,
6218  template_map->instance_size());
6219  template_map->set_instance_size(TemplateLiteralObject::kHeaderSize);
6220  // Temporarily instantiate a full template_literal_object to get the final
6221  // map.
6222  auto template_object =
6223  Cast<JSArray>(factory()->NewJSObjectFromMap(template_map));
6224  {
6225  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6226  Tagged<JSArray> raw = *template_object;
6227  raw->set_elements(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate()).empty_fixed_array());
6228  raw->set_length(Smi::FromInt(0));
6229  }
6230 
6231  // Install a "raw" data property for {raw_object} on {template_object}.
6232  // See ES#sec-gettemplateobject.
6233  PropertyDescriptor raw_desc;
6234  // Use arbrirary object {template_object} as ".raw" value.
6235  raw_desc.set_value(template_object);
6236  raw_desc.set_configurable(false);
6237  raw_desc.set_enumerable(false);
6238  raw_desc.set_writable(false);
6239  JSArray::DefineOwnProperty(isolate(), template_object,
6240  factory()->raw_string(), &raw_desc,
6241  Just(kThrowOnError))
6242  .ToChecked();
6243  // Install private symbol fields for function_literal_id and slot_id.
6244  raw_desc.set_value(direct_handle(Smi::zero(), isolate()));
6245  JSArray::DefineOwnProperty(
6246  isolate(), template_object,
6247  factory()->template_literal_function_literal_id_symbol(), &raw_desc,
6248  Just(kThrowOnError))
6249  .ToChecked();
6250  JSArray::DefineOwnProperty(isolate(), template_object,
6251  factory()->template_literal_slot_id_symbol(),
6252  &raw_desc, Just(kThrowOnError))
6253  .ToChecked();
6254 
6255  // Freeze the {template_object} as well.
6256  JSObject::SetIntegrityLevel(isolate(), template_object, FROZEN,
6257  kThrowOnError)
6258  .ToChecked();
6259  {
6260  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6261  Tagged<DescriptorArray> desc =
6262  template_object->map()->instance_descriptors();
6263  {
6264  // Verify TemplateLiteralObject::kRawOffset
6265  InternalIndex descriptor_index = desc->Search(
6266  *factory()->raw_string(), desc->number_of_descriptors());
6267  FieldIndex index =
6268  FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(template_object->map(), descriptor_index);
6269  CHECK(index.is_inobject());
6270  CHECK_EQ(index.offset(), TemplateLiteralObject::kRawOffset);
6271  }
6272 
6273  {
6274  // Verify TemplateLiteralObject::kFunctionLiteralIdOffset
6275  InternalIndex descriptor_index = desc->Search(
6276  *factory()->template_literal_function_literal_id_symbol(),
6277  desc->number_of_descriptors());
6278  FieldIndex index =
6279  FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(template_object->map(), descriptor_index);
6280  CHECK(index.is_inobject());
6281  CHECK_EQ(index.offset(),
6282  TemplateLiteralObject::kFunctionLiteralIdOffset);
6283  }
6284 
6285  {
6286  // Verify TemplateLiteralObject::kSlotIdOffset
6287  InternalIndex descriptor_index =
6288  desc->Search(*factory()->template_literal_slot_id_symbol(),
6289  desc->number_of_descriptors());
6290  FieldIndex index =
6291  FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(template_object->map(), descriptor_index);
6292  CHECK(index.is_inobject());
6293  CHECK_EQ(index.offset(), TemplateLiteralObject::kSlotIdOffset);
6294  }
6295  }
6296 
6297  native_context()->set_js_array_template_literal_object_map(
6298  template_object->map());
6299  }
6300 
6301  // Create a constructor for RegExp results (a variant of Array that
6302  // predefines the properties index, input, and groups).
6303  {
6304  // JSRegExpResult initial map.
6305  // Add additional slack to the initial map in case regexp_match_indices
6306  // are enabled to account for the additional descriptor.
6307  DirectHandle<Map> initial_map = CreateInitialMapForArraySubclass(
6308  JSRegExpResult::kSize, JSRegExpResult::kInObjectPropertyCount);
6309 
6310  // index descriptor.
6311  {
6312  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->index_string(),
6313  JSRegExpResult::kIndexIndex, NONE,
6314  Representation::Tagged());
6315  initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6316  }
6317 
6318  // input descriptor.
6319  {
6320  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->input_string(),
6321  JSRegExpResult::kInputIndex, NONE,
6322  Representation::Tagged());
6323  initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6324  }
6325 
6326  // groups descriptor.
6327  {
6328  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6329  isolate(), factory()->groups_string(), JSRegExpResult::kGroupsIndex,
6330  NONE, Representation::Tagged());
6331  initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6332  }
6333 
6334  // Private internal only fields. All of the remaining fields have special
6335  // symbols to prevent their use in Javascript.
6336  {
6337  PropertyAttributes attribs = DONT_ENUM;
6338 
6339  // names descriptor.
6340  {
6341  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6342  isolate(), factory()->regexp_result_names_symbol(),
6343  JSRegExpResult::kNamesIndex, attribs, Representation::Tagged());
6344  initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6345  }
6346 
6347  // regexp_input_index descriptor.
6348  {
6349  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6350  isolate(), factory()->regexp_result_regexp_input_symbol(),
6351  JSRegExpResult::kRegExpInputIndex, attribs,
6352  Representation::Tagged());
6353  initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6354  }
6355 
6356  // regexp_last_index descriptor.
6357  {
6358  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6359  isolate(), factory()->regexp_result_regexp_last_index_symbol(),
6360  JSRegExpResult::kRegExpLastIndex, attribs,
6361  Representation::Tagged());
6362  initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6363  }
6364  }
6365 
6366  // Set up the map for RegExp results objects for regexps with the /d flag.
6367  DirectHandle<Map> initial_with_indices_map =
6368  Map::Copy(isolate(), initial_map, "JSRegExpResult with indices");
6369  initial_with_indices_map->set_instance_size(
6370  JSRegExpResultWithIndices::kSize);
6371  DCHECK_EQ(initial_with_indices_map->GetInObjectProperties(),
6372  JSRegExpResultWithIndices::kInObjectPropertyCount);
6373 
6374  // indices descriptor
6375  {
6376  Descriptor d =
6377  Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->indices_string(),
6378  JSRegExpResultWithIndices::kIndicesIndex, NONE,
6379  Representation::Tagged());
6380  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), initial_with_indices_map, 1);
6381  initial_with_indices_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6382  }
6383 
6384  native_context()->set_regexp_result_map(*initial_map);
6385  native_context()->set_regexp_result_with_indices_map(
6386  *initial_with_indices_map);
6387  }
6388 
6389  // Create a constructor for JSRegExpResultIndices (a variant of Array that
6390  // predefines the groups property).
6391  {
6392  // JSRegExpResultIndices initial map.
6393  DirectHandle<Map> initial_map = CreateInitialMapForArraySubclass(
6394  JSRegExpResultIndices::kSize,
6395  JSRegExpResultIndices::kInObjectPropertyCount);
6396 
6397  // groups descriptor.
6398  {
6399  Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6400  isolate(), factory()->groups_string(),
6401  JSRegExpResultIndices::kGroupsIndex, NONE, Representation::Tagged());
6402  initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6403  DCHECK_EQ(initial_map->LastAdded().as_int(),
6404  JSRegExpResultIndices::kGroupsDescriptorIndex);
6405  }
6406 
6407  native_context()->set_regexp_result_indices_map(*initial_map);
6408  }
6409 
6410  // Add @@iterator method to the arguments object maps.
6411  {
6412  PropertyAttributes attribs = DONT_ENUM;
6413  DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> arguments_iterator =
6414  factory()->arguments_iterator_accessor();
6415  {
6416  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(factory()->iterator_symbol(),
6417  arguments_iterator, attribs);
6418  DirectHandle<Map> map(native_context()->sloppy_arguments_map(),
6419  isolate());
6420  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 1);
6421  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6422  }
6423  {
6424  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(factory()->iterator_symbol(),
6425  arguments_iterator, attribs);
6426  DirectHandle<Map> map(native_context()->fast_aliased_arguments_map(),
6427  isolate());
6428  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 1);
6429  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6430  }
6431  {
6432  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(factory()->iterator_symbol(),
6433  arguments_iterator, attribs);
6434  DirectHandle<Map> map(native_context()->slow_aliased_arguments_map(),
6435  isolate());
6436  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 1);
6437  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6438  }
6439  {
6440  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(factory()->iterator_symbol(),
6441  arguments_iterator, attribs);
6442  DirectHandle<Map> map(native_context()->strict_arguments_map(),
6443  isolate());
6444  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 1);
6445  map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6446  }
6447  }
6448  {
6449  DirectHandle<OrderedHashSet> promises =
6450  OrderedHashSet::Allocate(isolate(), 0).ToHandleChecked();
6451  native_context()->set_atomics_waitasync_promises(*promises);
6452  }
6453 
6454  return true;
6455 }

6489 void Genesis::InitializeMapCaches() {
6490  {
6491  DirectHandle<NormalizedMapCache> cache = NormalizedMapCache::New(isolate());
6492  native_context()->set_normalized_map_cache(*cache);
6493  }
6494 
6495  {
6496  DirectHandle<WeakFixedArray> cache = factory()->NewWeakFixedArray(
6497  JSObject::kMapCacheSize, AllocationType::kOld);
6498 
6499  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6500  for (int i = 0; i < JSObject::kMapCacheSize; i++) {
6501  cache->set(i, ClearedValue(isolate()));
6502  }
6503  native_context()->set_map_cache(*cache);
6504  Tagged<Map> initial = native_context()->object_function()->initial_map();
6505  cache->set(0, MakeWeak(initial));
6506  cache->set(initial->GetInObjectProperties(), MakeWeak(initial));
6507  }

6510 bool Bootstrapper::InstallExtensions(DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
6511  v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions) {
6512  // Don't install extensions into the snapshot.
6513  if (isolate_->serializer_enabled()) return true;
6514  BootstrapperActive active(this);
6515  v8::Context::Scope context_scope(Utils::ToLocal(native_context));
6516  return Genesis::InstallExtensions(isolate_, native_context, extensions) &&
6517  Genesis::InstallSpecialObjects(isolate_, native_context);
6518 }

6520 bool Genesis::InstallSpecialObjects(
6521  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context) {
6522  HandleScope scope(isolate);
6523 
6524  // Error.stackTraceLimit.
6525  {
6526  DirectHandle<JSObject> Error = isolate->error_function();
6527  DirectHandle<String> name = isolate->factory()->stackTraceLimit_string();
6528  DirectHandle<Smi> stack_trace_limit(
6529  Smi::FromInt(v8_flags.stack_trace_limit), isolate);
6530  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, Error, name, stack_trace_limit, NONE);
6531  }
6532 
6533 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6534  WasmJs::Install(isolate);
6535 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6536 
6537 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_CORRUPTION_API
6538  if (v8_flags.expose_memory_corruption_api) {
6539  SandboxTesting::InstallMemoryCorruptionApi(isolate);
6540  }
6541 #endif // V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_CORRUPTION_API
6542 
6543  return true;
6544 }

6546 static uint32_t Hash(RegisteredExtension* extension) {
6547  return v8::internal::ComputePointerHash(extension);
6548 }

6550 Genesis::ExtensionStates::ExtensionStates() : map_(8) {}
6551 
6552 Genesis::ExtensionTraversalState Genesis::ExtensionStates::get_state(
6553  RegisteredExtension* extension) {
6554  base::HashMap::Entry* entry = map_.Lookup(extension, Hash(extension));
6555  if (entry == nullptr) {
6556  return UNVISITED;
6557  }
6558  return static_cast<ExtensionTraversalState>(
6559  reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(entry->value));
6560 }
6561 
6562 void Genesis::ExtensionStates::set_state(RegisteredExtension* extension,
6563  ExtensionTraversalState state) {
6564  map_.LookupOrInsert(extension, Hash(extension))->value =
6565  reinterpret_cast<void*>(static_cast<intptr_t>(state));
6566 }
6567 
6568 bool Genesis::InstallExtensions(Isolate* isolate,
6569  DirectHandle<Context> native_context,
6570  v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions) {
6571  ExtensionStates extension_states; // All extensions have state UNVISITED.
6572  return InstallAutoExtensions(isolate, &extension_states) &&
6573  (!v8_flags.expose_gc ||
6574  InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/gc", &extension_states)) &&
6575  (!v8_flags.expose_externalize_string ||
6576  InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/externalize", &extension_states)) &&
6577  (!(v8_flags.expose_statistics ||
6578  TracingFlags::is_gc_stats_enabled()) ||
6579  InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/statistics", &extension_states)) &&
6580  (!v8_flags.expose_trigger_failure ||
6581  InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/trigger-failure", &extension_states)) &&
6582  (!v8_flags.expose_ignition_statistics ||
6583  InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/ignition-statistics",
6584  &extension_states)) &&
6585  (!isValidCpuTraceMarkFunctionName() ||
6586  InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/cpumark", &extension_states)) &&
6587 #ifdef V8_FUZZILLI
6588  InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/fuzzilli", &extension_states) &&
6589 #endif
6590 #ifdef ENABLE_VTUNE_TRACEMARK
6591  (!v8_flags.enable_vtune_domain_support ||
6592  InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/vtunedomain", &extension_states)) &&
6593 #endif // ENABLE_VTUNE_TRACEMARK
6594  InstallRequestedExtensions(isolate, extensions, &extension_states);
6595 }
6596 
6597 bool Genesis::InstallAutoExtensions(Isolate* isolate,
6598  ExtensionStates* extension_states) {
6599  for (v8::RegisteredExtension* it = v8::RegisteredExtension::first_extension();
6600  it != nullptr; it = it->next()) {
6601  if (it->extension()->auto_enable() &&
6602  !InstallExtension(isolate, it, extension_states)) {
6603  return false;
6604  }
6605  }
6606  return true;
6607 }
6608 
6609 bool Genesis::InstallRequestedExtensions(Isolate* isolate,
6610  v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions,
6611  ExtensionStates* extension_states) {
6612  for (const char** it = extensions->begin(); it != extensions->end(); ++it) {
6613  if (!InstallExtension(isolate, *it, extension_states)) return false;
6614  }
6615  return true;
6616 }
6617 
6618 // Installs a named extension. This methods is unoptimized and does
6619 // not scale well if we want to support a large number of extensions.
6620 bool Genesis::InstallExtension(Isolate* isolate, const char* name,
6621  ExtensionStates* extension_states) {
6622  for (v8::RegisteredExtension* it = v8::RegisteredExtension::first_extension();
6623  it != nullptr; it = it->next()) {
6624  if (strcmp(name, it->extension()->name()) == 0) {
6625  return InstallExtension(isolate, it, extension_states);
6626  }
6627  }
6628  return Utils::ApiCheck(false, "v8::Context::New()",
6629  "Cannot find required extension");
6630 }
6631 
6632 bool Genesis::InstallExtension(Isolate* isolate,
6633  v8::RegisteredExtension* current,
6634  ExtensionStates* extension_states) {
6635  HandleScope scope(isolate);
6636 
6637  if (extension_states->get_state(current) == INSTALLED) return true;
6638  // The current node has already been visited so there must be a
6639  // cycle in the dependency graph; fail.
6640  if (!Utils::ApiCheck(extension_states->get_state(current) != VISITED,
6641  "v8::Context::New()", "Circular extension dependency")) {
6642  return false;
6643  }
6644  DCHECK(extension_states->get_state(current) == UNVISITED);
6645  extension_states->set_state(current, VISITED);
6646  v8::Extension* extension = current->extension();
6647  // Install the extension's dependencies
6648  for (int i = 0; i < extension->dependency_count(); i++) {
6649  if (!InstallExtension(isolate, extension->dependencies()[i],
6650  extension_states)) {
6651  return false;
6652  }
6653  }
6654  if (!CompileExtension(isolate, extension)) {
6655  // We print out the name of the extension that fail to install.
6656  // When an error is thrown during bootstrapping we automatically print
6657  // the line number at which this happened to the console in the isolate
6658  // error throwing functionality.
6659  base::OS::PrintError("Error installing extension '%s'.\n",
6660  current->extension()->name());
6661  return false;
6662  }
6663 
6664  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
6665  extension_states->set_state(current, INSTALLED);
6666  return true;
6667 }
6668 
6669 bool Genesis::ConfigureGlobalObject(
6670  v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template) {
6671  DirectHandle<JSObject> global_proxy(native_context()->global_proxy(),
6672  isolate());
6673  DirectHandle<JSObject> global_object(native_context()->global_object(),
6674  isolate());
6675 
6676  if (!global_proxy_template.IsEmpty()) {
6677  // Configure the global proxy object.
6678  DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> global_proxy_data =
6679  v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global_proxy_template);
6680  if (!ConfigureApiObject(global_proxy, global_proxy_data)) {
6681  base::OS::PrintError("V8 Error: Failed to configure global_proxy_data\n");
6682  return false;
6683  }
6684 
6685  // Configure the global object.
6686  DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> proxy_constructor(
6687  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(global_proxy_data->constructor()),
6688  isolate());
6689  if (!IsUndefined(proxy_constructor->GetPrototypeTemplate(), isolate())) {
6690  DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> global_object_data(
6691  Cast<ObjectTemplateInfo>(proxy_constructor->GetPrototypeTemplate()),
6692  isolate());
6693  if (!ConfigureApiObject(global_object, global_object_data)) {
6694  base::OS::PrintError(
6695  "V8 Error: Failed to configure global_object_data\n");
6696  return false;
6697  }
6698  }
6699  }
6700 
6701  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), global_proxy, global_object);
6702 
6703  native_context()->set_array_buffer_map(
6704  native_context()->array_buffer_fun()->initial_map());
6705 
6706  return true;
6707 }
6708 
6709 bool Genesis::ConfigureApiObject(
6710  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
6711  DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> object_template) {
6712  DCHECK(!object_template.is_null());
6713  DCHECK(Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(object_template->constructor())
6714  ->IsTemplateFor(object->map()));
6715 
6716  MaybeDirectHandle<JSObject> maybe_obj =
6717  ApiNatives::InstantiateObject(isolate_, object_template);
6718  DirectHandle<JSObject> instantiated_template;
6719  if (!maybe_obj.ToHandle(&instantiated_template)) {
6720  DCHECK(isolate()->has_exception());
6721 
6722  DirectHandle<String> message =
6723  ErrorUtils::ToString(isolate_,
6724  direct_handle(isolate_->exception(), isolate_))
6725  .ToHandleChecked();
6726  base::OS::PrintError(
6727  "V8 Error: Exception in Genesis::ConfigureApiObject: %s\n",
6728  message->ToCString().get());
6729 
6730  isolate()->clear_exception();
6731  return false;
6732  }
6733  TransferObject(instantiated_template, object);
6734  return true;
6735 }
6736 
6737 static bool PropertyAlreadyExists(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> to,
6738  DirectHandle<Name> key) {
6739  LookupIterator it(isolate, to, key, LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
6740  CHECK_NE(LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK, it.state());
6741  return it.IsFound();
6742 }
6743 
6744 void Genesis::TransferNamedProperties(DirectHandle<JSObject> from,
6745  DirectHandle<JSObject> to) {
6746  // If JSObject::AddProperty asserts due to already existing property,
6747  // it is likely due to both global objects sharing property name(s).
6748  // Merging those two global objects is impossible.
6749  // The global template must not create properties that already exist
6750  // in the snapshotted global object.
6751  if (from->HasFastProperties()) {
6752  DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descs(
6753  from->map()->instance_descriptors(isolate()), isolate());
6754  for (InternalIndex i : from->map()->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
6755  PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
6756  if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
6757  if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
6758  HandleScope inner(isolate());
6759  DirectHandle<Name> key(descs->GetKey(i), isolate());
6760  // If the property is already there we skip it.
6761  if (PropertyAlreadyExists(isolate(), to, key)) continue;
6762  FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(from->map(), details);
6763  DirectHandle<Object> value = JSObject::FastPropertyAt(
6764  isolate(), from, details.representation(), index);
6765  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), to, key, value,
6766  details.attributes());
6767  } else {
6768  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
6769  UNREACHABLE();
6770  }
6771 
6772  } else {
6773  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kDescriptor, details.location());
6774  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
6775  DirectHandle<Name> key(descs->GetKey(i), isolate());
6776  // If the property is already there we skip it.
6777  if (PropertyAlreadyExists(isolate(), to, key)) continue;
6778  HandleScope inner(isolate());
6779  DCHECK(!to->HasFastProperties());
6780  // Add to dictionary.
6781  DirectHandle<Object> value(descs->GetStrongValue(i), isolate());
6782  PropertyDetails d(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.attributes(),
6783  PropertyCellType::kMutable);
6784  JSObject::SetNormalizedProperty(to, key, value, d);
6785  }
6786  }
6787  } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(*from)) {
6788  // Copy all keys and values in enumeration order.
6789  DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> properties(
6790  Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*from)->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad),
6791  isolate());
6792  DirectHandle<FixedArray> indices =
6793  GlobalDictionary::IterationIndices(isolate(), properties);
6794  for (int i = 0; i < indices->length(); i++) {
6795  InternalIndex index(Smi::ToInt(indices->get(i)));
6796  DirectHandle<PropertyCell> cell(properties->CellAt(index), isolate());
6797  DirectHandle<Name> key(cell->name(), isolate());
6798  // If the property is already there we skip it.
6799  if (PropertyAlreadyExists(isolate(), to, key)) continue;
6800  // Set the property.
6801  DirectHandle<Object> value(cell->value(), isolate());
6802  if (IsTheHole(*value, isolate())) continue;
6803  PropertyDetails details = cell->property_details();
6804  if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
6805  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), to, key, value, details.attributes());
6806  } else {
6807  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
6808  DCHECK(!to->HasFastProperties());
6809  PropertyDetails d(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.attributes(),
6810  PropertyCellType::kMutable);
6811  JSObject::SetNormalizedProperty(to, key, value, d);
6812  }
6813  }
6814 
6815  } else if (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
6816  // Copy all keys and values in enumeration order.
6817  DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> properties(
6818  from->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate());
6819  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
6820  for (InternalIndex entry : properties->IterateEntriesOrdered()) {
6821  Tagged<Object> raw_key;
6822  if (!properties->ToKey(roots, entry, &raw_key)) continue;
6823 
6824  DCHECK(IsName(raw_key));
6825  DirectHandle<Name> key(Cast<Name>(raw_key), isolate());
6826  // If the property is already there we skip it.
6827  if (PropertyAlreadyExists(isolate(), to, key)) continue;
6828  // Set the property.
6829  DirectHandle<Object> value(properties->ValueAt(entry), isolate());
6830  DCHECK(!IsCell(*value));
6831  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(*value, isolate()));
6832  PropertyDetails details = properties->DetailsAt(entry);
6833  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
6834  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), to, key, value, details.attributes());
6835  }
6836  } else {
6837  // Copy all keys and values in enumeration order.
6838  DirectHandle<NameDictionary> properties(from->property_dictionary(),
6839  isolate());
6840  DirectHandle<FixedArray> key_indices =
6841  NameDictionary::IterationIndices(isolate(), properties);
6842  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
6843  for (int i = 0; i < key_indices->length(); i++) {
6844  InternalIndex key_index(Smi::ToInt(key_indices->get(i)));
6845  Tagged<Object> raw_key = properties->KeyAt(key_index);
6846  DCHECK(properties->IsKey(roots, raw_key));
6847  DCHECK(IsName(raw_key));
6848  DirectHandle<Name> key(Cast<Name>(raw_key), isolate());
6849  // If the property is already there we skip it.
6850  if (PropertyAlreadyExists(isolate(), to, key)) continue;
6851  // Set the property.
6852  DirectHandle<Object> value(properties->ValueAt(key_index), isolate());
6853  DCHECK(!IsCell(*value));
6854  DCHECK(!IsTheHole(*value, isolate()));
6855  PropertyDetails details = properties->DetailsAt(key_index);
6856  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
6857  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), to, key, value, details.attributes());
6858  }
6859  }
6860 }
6861 
6862 void Genesis::TransferIndexedProperties(DirectHandle<JSObject> from,
6863  DirectHandle<JSObject> to) {
6864  // Cloning the elements array is sufficient.
6865  Handle<FixedArray> from_elements(Cast<FixedArray>(from->elements()),
6866  isolate());
6867  DirectHandle<FixedArray> to_elements =
6868  factory()->CopyFixedArray(from_elements);
6869  to->set_elements(*to_elements);
6870 }
6871 
6872 void Genesis::TransferObject(DirectHandle<JSObject> from,
6873  DirectHandle<JSObject> to) {
6874  HandleScope outer(isolate());
6875 
6876  DCHECK(!IsJSArray(*from));
6877  DCHECK(!IsJSArray(*to));
6878 
6879  TransferNamedProperties(from, to);
6880  TransferIndexedProperties(from, to);
6881 
6882  // Transfer the prototype (new map is needed).
6883  DirectHandle<JSPrototype> proto(from->map()->prototype(), isolate());
6884  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), to, proto);
6885 }
6886 
6887 DirectHandle<Map> Genesis::CreateInitialMapForArraySubclass(
6888  int size, int inobject_properties) {
6889  // Find global.Array.prototype to inherit from.
6890  DirectHandle<JSFunction> array_constructor(native_context()->array_function(),
6891  isolate());
6892  DirectHandle<JSObject> array_prototype(
6893  native_context()->initial_array_prototype(), isolate());
6894 
6895  // Add initial map.
6896  DirectHandle<Map> initial_map = factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
6897  JS_ARRAY_TYPE, size, TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, inobject_properties);
6898  initial_map->SetConstructor(*array_constructor);
6899 
6900  // Set prototype on map.
6901  initial_map->set_has_non_instance_prototype(false);
6902  Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), initial_map, array_prototype);
6903 
6904  // Update map with length accessor from Array.
6905  static constexpr int kTheLengthAccessor = 1;
6906  Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), initial_map,
6907  inobject_properties + kTheLengthAccessor);
6908 
6909  // length descriptor.
6910  {
6911  Tagged<JSFunction> array_function = native_context()->array_function();
6912  DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> array_descriptors(
6913  array_function->initial_map()->instance_descriptors(isolate()),
6914  isolate());
6915  DirectHandle<String> length = factory()->length_string();
6916  InternalIndex old = array_descriptors->SearchWithCache(
6917  isolate(), *length, array_function->initial_map());
6918  DCHECK(old.is_found());
6919  Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
6920  length,
6921  direct_handle(array_descriptors->GetStrongValue(old), isolate()),
6922  array_descriptors->GetDetails(old).attributes());
6923  initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6924  }
6925  return initial_map;
6926 }
6927 
6928 Genesis::Genesis(Isolate* isolate,
6929  MaybeDirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
6930  v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
6931  size_t context_snapshot_index,
6932  DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
6933  v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue)
6934  : isolate_(isolate), active_(isolate->bootstrapper()) {
6935  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kGenesis);
6936  result_ = {};
6937  global_proxy_ = {};
6938 
6939  // Before creating the roots we must save the context and restore it
6940  // on all function exits.
6941  SaveContext saved_context(isolate);
6942 
6943  // The deserializer needs to hook up references to the global proxy.
6944  // Create an uninitialized global proxy now if we don't have one
6945  // and initialize it later in CreateNewGlobals.
6946  DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy;
6947  if (!maybe_global_proxy.ToHandle(&global_proxy)) {
6948  int instance_size = 0;
6949  if (context_snapshot_index > 0) {
6950  // The global proxy function to reinitialize this global proxy is in the
6951  // context that is yet to be deserialized. We need to prepare a global
6952  // proxy of the correct size.
6953  Tagged<Object> size =
6954  isolate->heap()->serialized_global_proxy_sizes()->get(
6955  static_cast<int>(context_snapshot_index) -
6956  SnapshotCreatorImpl::kFirstAddtlContextIndex);
6957  instance_size = Smi::ToInt(size);
6958  } else {
6959  instance_size = JSGlobalProxy::SizeWithEmbedderFields(
6960  global_proxy_template.IsEmpty()
6961  ? 0
6962  : global_proxy_template->InternalFieldCount());
6963  }
6964  global_proxy =
6965  isolate->factory()->NewUninitializedJSGlobalProxy(instance_size);
6966  }
6967 
6968  // We can only de-serialize a context if the isolate was initialized from
6969  // a snapshot. Otherwise we have to build the context from scratch.
6970  // Also create a context from scratch to expose natives, if required by flag.
6971  DCHECK(native_context_.is_null());
6972  if (isolate->initialized_from_snapshot()) {
6973  DirectHandle<Context> context;
6974  if (Snapshot::NewContextFromSnapshot(isolate, global_proxy,
6975  context_snapshot_index,
6976  embedder_fields_deserializer)
6977  .ToHandle(&context)) {
6978  native_context_ = Cast<NativeContext>(context);
6979  }
6980  }
6981 
6982  if (!native_context().is_null()) {
6983  AddToWeakNativeContextList(isolate, *native_context());
6984  isolate->set_context(*native_context());
6985 
6986  // If no global proxy template was passed in, simply use the global in the
6987  // snapshot. If a global proxy template was passed in it's used to recreate
6988  // the global object and its prototype chain, and the data and the accessor
6989  // properties from the deserialized global are copied onto it.
6990  if (context_snapshot_index == 0 && !global_proxy_template.IsEmpty()) {
6991  DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object =
6992  CreateNewGlobals(global_proxy_template, global_proxy);
6993  HookUpGlobalObject(global_object);
6994  if (!ConfigureGlobalObject(global_proxy_template)) return;
6995  } else {
6996  // The global proxy needs to be integrated into the native context.
6997  HookUpGlobalProxy(global_proxy);
6998  }
6999  DCHECK_EQ(global_proxy->GetCreationContext(), *native_context());
7000  DCHECK(!global_proxy->IsDetachedFrom(isolate,
7001  native_context()->global_object()));
7002  } else {
7003  DCHECK(native_context().is_null());
7004 
7005  Isolate::EnableRoAllocationForSnapshotScope enable_ro_allocation(isolate);
7006 
7007  base::ElapsedTimer timer;
7008  if (v8_flags.profile_deserialization) timer.Start();
7009  DCHECK_EQ(0u, context_snapshot_index);
7010  // We get here if there was no context snapshot.
7011  CreateRoots();
7012  MathRandom::InitializeContext(isolate, native_context());
7013  DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function = CreateEmptyFunction();
7014  CreateSloppyModeFunctionMaps(empty_function);
7015  CreateStrictModeFunctionMaps(empty_function);
7016  CreateObjectFunction(empty_function);
7017  CreateIteratorMaps(empty_function);
7018  CreateAsyncIteratorMaps(empty_function);
7019  CreateAsyncFunctionMaps(empty_function);
7020  DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object =
7021  CreateNewGlobals(global_proxy_template, global_proxy);
7022  InitializeMapCaches();
7023  InitializeGlobal(global_object, empty_function);
7024  InitializeIteratorFunctions();
7025  InitializeCallSiteBuiltins();
7026 
7027  if (!InstallABunchOfRandomThings()) return;
7028  if (!InstallExtrasBindings()) return;
7029  if (!ConfigureGlobalObject(global_proxy_template)) return;
7030 
7031 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
7032  WasmJs::PrepareForSnapshot(isolate);
7033 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
7034 
7035  if (v8_flags.profile_deserialization) {
7036  double ms = timer.Elapsed().InMillisecondsF();
7037  PrintF("[Initializing context from scratch took %0.3f ms]\n", ms);
7038  }
7039  }
7040 
7041  native_context()->set_microtask_queue(
7042  isolate, microtask_queue ? static_cast<MicrotaskQueue*>(microtask_queue)
7043  : isolate->default_microtask_queue());
7044 
7045  // Install experimental natives. Do not include them into the
7046  // snapshot as we should be able to turn them off at runtime. Re-installing
7047  // them after they have already been deserialized would also fail.
7048  if (!isolate->serializer_enabled()) {
7049  InitializeExperimentalGlobal();
7050 
7051  // Store String.prototype's map again in case it has been changed by
7052  // experimental natives.
7053  DirectHandle<JSFunction> string_function(
7054  native_context()->string_function(), isolate);
7055  Tagged<JSObject> string_function_prototype =
7056  Cast<JSObject>(string_function->initial_map()->prototype());
7057  DCHECK(string_function_prototype->HasFastProperties());
7058  native_context()->set_string_function_prototype_map(
7059  string_function_prototype->map());
7060  }
7061 
7062  if (v8_flags.disallow_code_generation_from_strings) {
7063  native_context()->set_allow_code_gen_from_strings(
7064  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).false_value());
7065  }
7066 
7067  // We created new functions, which may require debug instrumentation.
7068  if (isolate->debug()->is_active()) {
7069  isolate->debug()->InstallDebugBreakTrampoline();
7070  }
7071 
7072  native_context()->ResetErrorsThrown();
7073  result_ = native_context();
7074 }
7075 
7076 Genesis::Genesis(Isolate* isolate,
7077  MaybeDirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
7078  v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template)
7079  : isolate_(isolate), active_(isolate->bootstrapper()) {
7080  result_ = {};
7081  global_proxy_ = {};
7082 
7083  // Before creating the roots we must save the context and restore it
7084  // on all function exits.
7085  SaveContext saved_context(isolate);
7086 
7087  const int proxy_size = JSGlobalProxy::SizeWithEmbedderFields(
7088  global_proxy_template->InternalFieldCount());
7089 
7090  DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy;
7091  if (maybe_global_proxy.ToHandle(&global_proxy)) {
7092  global_proxy->map()->set_map(isolate, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).meta_map());
7093  } else {
7094  global_proxy = factory()->NewUninitializedJSGlobalProxy(proxy_size);
7095  }
7096 
7097  // Create a remote object as the global object.
7098  DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> global_proxy_data =
7099  Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global_proxy_template);
7100  DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> global_constructor(
7101  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(global_proxy_data->constructor()), isolate);
7102 
7103  DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> global_object_template(
7104  Cast<ObjectTemplateInfo>(global_constructor->GetPrototypeTemplate()),
7105  isolate);
7106  DirectHandle<JSObject> global_object =
7107  ApiNatives::InstantiateRemoteObject(global_object_template)
7108  .ToHandleChecked();
7109 
7110  // (Re)initialize the global proxy object.
7111  DCHECK_EQ(global_proxy_data->embedder_field_count(),
7112  global_proxy_template->InternalFieldCount());
7113  DirectHandle<Map> global_proxy_map = factory()->NewContextlessMap(
7114  JS_GLOBAL_PROXY_TYPE, proxy_size, TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND);
7115  global_proxy_map->set_is_access_check_needed(true);
7116  global_proxy_map->set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
7117 
7118  // Configure the hidden prototype chain of the global proxy.
7119  JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate, global_proxy, global_object);
7120  global_proxy->map()->SetConstructor(*global_constructor);
7121 
7122  global_proxy_ = global_proxy;
7123 }

7127 // Reserve space for statics needing saving and restoring.
7128 int Bootstrapper::ArchiveSpacePerThread() { return sizeof(NestingCounterType); }
7129 
7130 // Archive statics that are thread-local.
7131 char* Bootstrapper::ArchiveState(char* to) {
7132  *reinterpret_cast<NestingCounterType*>(to) = nesting_;
7133  nesting_ = 0;
7134  return to + sizeof(NestingCounterType);
7135 }
7136 
7137 // Restore statics that are thread-local.
7138 char* Bootstrapper::RestoreState(char* from) {
7139  nesting_ = *reinterpret_cast<NestingCounterType*>(from);
7140  return from + sizeof(NestingCounterType);
7141 }

7144 void Bootstrapper::FreeThreadResources() { DCHECK(!IsActive()); }
